Commentary: On the money right away. Full and around off, swinging in, watchfully defended.
Good running. Around off, Raval pushes this towards cover and sets off quickly. The fielders are caught off guard and a single is easily taken. The Test match scoreboard starts ticking.
Full and outside off, no swing on this one, left alone.
NOT FAR FROM SHORT LEG! Heart-in-mouth moment for Latham. Down the leg side, Tom tucks it aerially and just wide of short leg. A run taken to get both the openers off the mark.

Bizarre from umpire Illingworth. Down the leg side, Jeet looked to tuck it away but missed and the ball went off his thighs behind. Niroshan Dickwella dived to his right and got a glove to it, parrying it towards fine leg and taking some pace off it. The batsmen took a single but the umpire signalled a dead ball! Probably he felt that Raval was not offering a shot but replays do not seem to indicate so.
Full and around off, Suranga switching to around the wicket, watchfully defended. A good opening over from Lakmal.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
On a length around middle and leg, angling away, Latham watchfully shoulders arms.
Full and straight, well blocked out.
A bouncer but down the leg side, calmly ducked under.
Excellent delivery. On a length outside off, from around the stumps, coming in a long way off the deck, Raval looks to defend but is beaten by the movement. Gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Outside off, a touch wide, coming in but not bothering the batsman, shouldered arms to.
Full and outside off, wide again, let through once more.
Another wide ball outside off, Jeet is not interested.
On a length outside off, coming in, punched straight to cover.
Outside off, Jeet taps it towards cover and sets off for a single but is sent back as three fielders come charging in.
Full and down the leg side, pitching outside leg, Latham looks to flick but misses. Is hit outside leg as well as the LBW cries of the Lankans die down pretty quickly.
Outside off, pushed towards cover.
Full and down the leg side, flicked through square leg for a single.
Outside off, Jeet guides it towards third man, with soft hands but Kusal Mendis at second slip dives to his left and makes a brilliant stop.
Very full, around off, pushed back to the bowler.
This is full again, almost a yorker, dug out back to Kumara once more.
On a length outside off, left alone.
A length ball outside off, but too wide. Calmly left alone.
Another leave outside off.
Yawn. Full. Wide. Does the area matter? Not to either of the batsmen. Anyways, just so that you can picture how the action happened, this was outside off. Left alone.
Full and around middle, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone again.
FOUR! Nice shot. Full and around off, Raval leans and drives it through the covers for a boundary!
On middle and leg, tucked to the leg side.
On middle, helped past short leg for a single.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, on a length, let through.
Very full, around off, pushed towards mid on.
Some change of angle but the line is still poor. Down the leg side, left alone.
Another one down the leg side.
Outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Better ball. Outside off, at an angle which can cause the batsman to play, from around the wicket, but Raval lets it go.
Down the leg side, worked through square leg for a couple.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Full and around leg and middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and around leg, paddled through fine leg for a couple.
The batsman has been struck on the thigh pad. They pick up a single. Leg byes given by the umpire.
Full and just outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up, around off, Raval lunges and pushes this back to Akila.
Down the leg side, Jeet goes back and works it straight to short leg.
On a length wide outside off, shouldered arms to.
On a length, just outside off, coming in, watchfully pushed towards cover.
Back of a length this time, well blocked out.

Oohhh... saved by the bounce! On a good length outside off, Latham shoulders arms. But the ball swings in a long way and goes just over the stumps! Would have hit them, had it not been for the bounce.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
A length ball outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up around off, Latham comes forward and defends it in front of short leg.
Full and around off, paddled past short leg for a single.
Landed around off, a bit of loop, watchfully pushed towards point.

Full and around off, Tom looks to paddle again but this time the ball takes the under edge and goes wide of short leg. TL looks for a single but leg slip quickly gets across and Raval sends his partner back.
Outside off, punched through the covers for a run.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.

Good bowling but Lakmal oversteps. NO BALL. It was a decent nut, angling in from outside off, Latham looked to defend but was cut into half by the late movement. Ahh... replays show that Lakmal had something behind the line. Tough luck.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Full and outside off, Tom takes his bat away from the line.
Full and outside off, first mistake from TL as he looks to push at a wider one and is beaten. This is due to that inward movement on the no ball which was not a no ball earlier in the over...
On a length outside off, coming in, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, driven straight to cover.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Landed around middle, angling away, left alone.
A bouncer, dug in at halfway down the pitch, Raval watches it closely and sways away in time.
Fuller in length, driven straight down the ground but without any timing. Mid on cuts it off.

Misfield from the skipper. Full and outside off, Jeet drives it down the ground. Dimuth Karunaratne at mid off quickly gets across to his left but while trying to field the ball, he misjudges it and the cherry goes off his body behind. He quickly gets up and chases it down, preventing a boundary but two runs are taken by then.
Outside off, punched to the off side.
Full and outside off, spinning away, left alone.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.

Full and outside off, Latham looks to paddle but misses. It is a good thing that Niroshan Dickwella caught that. Because had he missed, Dhananjaya de Silva, at first slip, in his excitement to get to the ball in case Latham connected, had gone too far across and had to change track. Slipped.
Lovely bowling. Slower through the air, landing outside off, Tom looks to defend but the ball spins away and beats the outside edge.
A touch short, down the leg side, helped through square leg for a couple.
A short ball, around off, Raval sways away.
Another bouncer, ducked under this time.
Third bouncer on the trot, swayed away now.
Make that four bouncers in a row, Jeet sways away from the line.
Pitched outside leg, 145 kph, JR is beaten by pace as he looks to flick and is hit on the pads.
Full and around middle, flicked to deep mid-wicket for one.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Landed around off, Jeet looks to defend but the ball spins past the outside edge.
Outside off, left alone.
One more leave outside off.
Landed outside off, guided through third man for a couple.
Landed outside off, punched towards cover.
FOUR! Fine shot. Just the second boundary of the morning. Outside off, Latham leans and punches it through the covers.
Down the leg side, Tom misses his flick and is hit on the pads.
Outside off, let through.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On a length around off, TL taps it wide of mid on and takes a quick single.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and outside off, Latham looks to defend but misses.
Outside off, Tom looks to push but misses. Extravagant turn.
Down the leg side, helped through mid-wicket. Mid on gets to the ball to stop when it has already stopped and parries it back to mid-wicket. Three runs taken.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and outside off, Jeet lunges to defend but the ball spins away and beats the outside edge.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Short and outside off, cut straight to point.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot. They pick up a single.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Full and down the leg side, Jeet gets down and paddles it past the keeper towards fine leg. Two runs taken.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Gets down, takes this on the full and paddles it fine down the leg side for a single.
Short and outside off, Raval cuts it through the covers where the fielder makes a good stop to his right. A run taken.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, punched through the covers where Karunaratne makes a good stop.
Full and around off, worked through mid-wicket for a couple.
FOUR! LOVELY! Full and outside off, Raval leans and drives it wide of mid off for a boundary!
Outside off, punched to the off side.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
FOUR! Interesting choice of a shot. Tossed up outside off, Raval leans and lofts this over wide mid off for a boundary! Are these signs of wanting to take the spinners on?
On middle and leg, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Short and outside off, cut straight to point.
Full and around off, watchfully defended
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Nicely played. Full and around off, Latham gets down and sweeps it through square leg.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On middle and leg, helped through the leg side for a single.
Full and down the leg side, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
Outside off, tapped to the off side for a quick run.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
Around off, watchfully blocked out.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman.
Very nicely played. Landed outside off, Raval goes back and plays it very late past first slip towards third man for a couple.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
Short and outside off, cut through point for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Safe as a house. Full and outside off, Latham lunges to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes to short third man. Latham is doubtful about the run but Raval always wanted it and calls him through. Kusal Mendis fires a direct hit at the striker's end and it is referred upstairs. But replays show that Raval is well in.
FOUR! Short and outside off, Latham goes back and cuts it behind point for a boundary!
Landed outside off, Latham looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and wears it on his pads.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Goes back and blocks this one.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full and around off, Raval lunges to defend.
THAT STAYS LOW. It is on a length, spinning away from off, Jeet adjusts well on the back foot to punch it through the covers for a single.
Thrown up outside off, Latham comes forward and pushes it towards short leg.
Tossed up around off, Tom comes forward and blocks it out to the off side this time.
Around leg and middle, spinning away, pushed back to the bowler.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Around off, worked towards short leg.
Full and around middle and leg, worked to the leg side.
Around middle and leg, flicked wide of mid on for a single.
Full and around off, pushed towards the bowler.
Comes down the track and pushes it towards mid on.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Tossed up around leg stump, Raval looks to flick it to the leg side but the ball spins away and takes the leading edge towards cover.
Outside leg, this time Jeet plays it straighter, pushing it towards mid on for a quick single.

OUT! Caught behind! Akila Dananjaya has provided the first breakthrough of this Test. A bit of an indecision from Latham here. Landed around off, Tom goes back to defend but then looks to withdraw his bat as an afterthought. Is caught in no man's land as he does a bit of both and hangs his bat midway. The ball pitches, turns and takes a feather of an outside edge behind. Niroshan Dickwella collects and leaps in celebration. The umpire raises his finger and Latham does not wait. End of a 64-run stand.
Full and outside off, pushed towards mid off.
Around middle and off, worked towards mid-wicket.

OUT! Caught! Second wicket in the over and the Kiwi captain is gone for a duck. Big, big blow. The match has spun big time. From going nowhere, sending people into dreams with yawns, now, with a quarter of an hour to go to Lunch, everyone has been stirred awake. Landed outside off, Williamson comes forward initially, but then goes back, looking to work it into the leg side. He cannot keep it down and finds Dimuth Karunaratne at short mid-wicket who takes it easily! Sri Lanka have their tail up now.
Around off, punched off the back foot.
Full and around off, Raval lunges and pushes it back to the bowler.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Outside off, Raval goes back and defends it from his crease.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, Taylor goes back to defend but the ball skids on after pitching and squared Rosco up, going off the outside edge towards cover.
The wrong 'un now, outside off, RT picks it and looks to drive but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Outside off, flicked straight to short leg where Kusal Mendis quickly flicks it back to the keeper. Dickwella takes the bails off but Taylor is in.
Landed outside off, spinning down, Rosco goes back and tucks it past leg slip for a single.
Full and around middle, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, pushed towards cover.
Landed outside off, Taylor goes back and plays it with the away spin towards cover.
Full and down the leg side, Rosco gets down and sweeps it fine. Akila Dananjaya gives it a good chase and flicks it back in, with a dive near the boundary. Three runs taken.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, spinning in, worked through mid-wicket for a single.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Full and around off, Rosco flicks it through mid-wicket where Angelo Mathews dives and parries it wide of mid on. A run taken.
Short and outside off, Taylor cuts it through point where Lahiru Kumara dives to his left and makes a half-stop. A quick single taken.

OUT! Edged and taken! Third wicket down in the span of 16 minutes! What a spur of life this mini-spell has brought about. Full and outside off, Raval lunges to defend but the ball hits the pitch and Jeet expects it to spin away. Hence, to miss it. But this is the doosra. It comes in, takes the outside edge and goes low to first slip where Dhananjaya de Silva takes it by coming forward. LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Full and around off, nice pace and flight, Nicholls pushes it back to the bowler.
A touch short, Henry goes back and pushes it back to Akila once again.
Quicker outside off, the southpaw is solid in defense from his crease.
Full and around off, pushed back to AD.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Comes down the track and pushes it towards mid on.
Full and outside off, driven through the covers where the fielder makes a good stop to his left.

Excitement all around but nothing from the umpire. Full and outside leg, Taylor gets down to sweep but misses. The ball hits his pads and is taken by Kusal Mendis at short leg but there is not much of an appeal.
Full and outside off, Rosco comes down the track and drives it towards cover.
FOUR! HAMMERED! Full and around middle, Taylor gets down and mows a slog sweep over mid-wicket!
Full and outside off, Nicholls comes forward and shoulders arms to one spinning away.
Tossed up, outside off, pushed towards the bowler.
Landed outside off, Henry is squared up and pushes it awkwardly to the off side.
Around middle, HN thrusts his pads in front and blocks this with the bat to the leg side.
FOUR! Very good shot. Tossed up, around middle, Nicholls gets his big reach out, gets down and sweeps it in front of square on the leg side.

Outside off, Nicholls punches it towards cover. Dimuth Karunaratne fields and has a needless shy at the bowler's end, despite Taylor being well in his crease. Misses and by the time Angelo Mathews can track it down from mid-wicket, two runs are taken.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Around off, watchfully pushed back.
Full and around middle, Taylor comes down the track and lofts it over mid on. The ball stops near the ropes and Lahiru Kumara gets to it with a valiant chase. Three  runs taken.
Full and around off, watchfully blocked out.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
On middle and leg, turned towards square leg.
Slowly tossed up, outside off, watchfully defended.
Goes back and turns it through square leg for a single.
That is a ripper. Akila lands this around middle, Nicholls goes back to defend but then the ball spins away past the outside edge.

Good fielding. Dananjaya drops this a bit short outside off and Henry goes back and punches it through the covers. Lasith Embuldeniya gives it a good chase from cover and slides to his left to keep the batsmen to a single.
Outside off, spinning in, worked towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
Full and down the leg side, HN looks to sweep but the ball hits his glove and goes off Niroshan Dickwella's boots towards first slip.
Hmmm.... this is how Taylor plays. Tossed up outside off, Rosco looks to play the cover drive with hard hands but misses. Niroshan Dickwella behind fumbles but takes it in the second attempt.
Full and around middle, pushed towards short mid-wicket.
Outside off, eased towards the bowler on Taylor's off side.

FOUR! IMPERIOUS! Taylor is at his best when he is looking to play such shots. Jumps down the track, gets to the pitch of this ball, which is flighted outside off on a fuller length and hammers it past the bowler to beat mid off.

This is what happens when a batsman plays a shot similar to the one on the previous delivery. Mid off is pushed back. Why? Very bizarre. Rosco comes down the track and drives it towards long off for a comfortable single.
Now Nicholls comes down the track, takes this on the full and bunts this to long on for a run.
Full and around off, Nicholls lunges to defend.
Slowly bowled through the air, on a fuller length around off, Henry comes forward to defend but is beaten by the massive off spin.
Full and down the leg side, swept to deep square leg for a single.
Full and around off, pushed towards long on for a run.
Full and down the leg side, Nicholls gets down and sweeps it behind square leg. Lahiru Kumara chases it down from deep mid-wicket and dives to his left to stop the ball. Two runs taken.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flighted outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Comes down the track and pushes it towards long on for a single.
Outside off, Nicholls goes back and defends.
Full and around middle, pushed towards long on for a run.
Slowly pushed through the air, around middle and leg, Taylor looks to defend but the ball takes the inside edge and goes on the bounce to short leg.
Uses his feet this time to drive this towards long off for one. 100 UP FOR NEW ZEALAND.
Doosra from Akila, landing outside off, short in length, Taylor picks it up in a trice and looks to cut but is beaten by pace.
Around off, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, pushed towards cover.
Full and around off, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Tossed up with hardly any pace outside off, Rosco defends it watchfully.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
A short ball, around leg, worked through mid-wicket for a single.

Tossed up outside off, Taylor comes down the track and drives it through the covers where Dimuth Karunaratne at short extra cover dives to his right to take some sting off the ball. Parries it to long off and a run is taken.
Around off, watchfully defended.
Comes down the track and flicks it off the inner half but it flies wide of short leg.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Pushes this to long on for a run.
Full and around middle, swept behind square leg for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Short and outside off, punched down to long on for another easy run. Sri Lanka just seem to be giving away the advantage at the moment.
Full and around off, pushed to the leg side.
Plenty of loop outside off, Nicholls lunges to defend but ends up yorking himself.
Short and outside off, cut straight to point.
Full and around middle, Taylor gets down and sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Around middle and leg, helped through square leg for a run.
Comes down the track and pushes it through mid on for one more.
Around off, solidly defended.
Around middle, helped towards short leg.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Around off, worked through mid-wicket for a single.
Fired in around middle, Nicholls looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Outside off, pushed towards cover.
Landed outside off, punched towards cover.
Outside off, pushed towards point.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Landed around off, driven straight to short extra cover.
FOUR! MURDERED! Fractionally short and around off, Taylor goes back and pulls it over short mid-wicket for a boundary!
Rosco comes down the track but is not quite to the pitch of the ball. Looks to defend but gets a thick inside edge onto his pads.
Outside off, punched towards cover.
Full and around middle, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
More runs on the off side. This is short and outside off, Nicholls goes back and cuts it behind point. Lasith Embuldeniya chases it down from backward point and pulls it back in. Two runs taken.
Landed outside off, left alone.
Outside off, punched through the covers for a single.
Fired in around off, punched towards mid on but short mid-wicket mops it up.
Full and around middle, pushed towards short mid-wicket.
Eases this down to long on for a run.
Full and outside off, Taylor leans and drives this through the covers for a couple.
Around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Around off, worked wide of mid on for a single.
Full and just around off, watchfully defended.
Full and outside off, Nicholls pushes it with soft hands and gets it through the slip cordon for a couple. 50-RUN STAND IS UP. Excellent recovery.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Fired in on middle, pushed towards long on for a single.

MISCOMMUNICATION, SAFE! Big miss by Karunaratne. Outside off, Nicholls pushes it towards cover and sets off for a single. But then, he stutters and stops. Taylor starts and stops too, looking at that. Eventually, they decide to go through and Rosco is gone for all money but Karunaratne returns a wild throw to Dickwella, which is very wide to his right and Taylor gets in.
Gets down, takes it on the full and paddles it through fine leg for a run.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Around off, pushed back to Dhananjaya again.
Outside off, Taylor looks to punch but gets a bottom edge to the off side.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Gets across his stumps and looks to tuck but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes towards fine leg and a leg bye is taken.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Outside off, left alone.
Full and around off, well kept out.
Tossed up outside leg, Taylor pads it away.
Short and around off, flicked through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and outside off, Nicholls lunges and takes his bat away.
Fired in on middle, pushed towards cover.
Comes down the track and works it towards short mid-wicket.
Full and around off, well defended.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off, pushed through the covers for a couple.
Full and outside off, solidly defended towards mid on.
Outside off, solidly defended.
Outside off, played through point for a single.
On middle and leg, tucked through mid-wicket for a run.
Full and around middle, Nicholls gets down and sweeps it through square leg for a single.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Comes down the track and bunts it through mid on for a run.
Full and around off, Henry gets down and sweeps this through mid-wicket. Very effective shot to the left-arm spinner. A single taken.
Short and outside off, cut behind point for a brace.

Excellent stop by Kusal Mendis. Full and outside off, Taylor sweeps this powerfully through square leg but Kusal Mendis at short leg brings out excellent reflexes to stick out his left leg. Cannot stop the ball cleanly but concedes only a single.
Full and outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Pushes this towards mid on.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full and around off, pushed back towards the bowler.
This one jags back in, Rosco looks to defend but the ball goes off the inside edge towards square leg.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Massive, loud screeches for LBW. Nothing doing. Full and outside off, Nicholls gets well outside the line, looking to sweep. Misses but is hit on the shoulder miles outside off.
Full and around off, this is swept powerfully through mid-wicket for a single.
Around off, pushed towards cover.
Outside off, eased through cover and point for a run.
Full and down the leg side, swept through mid-wicket for one.
Full and outside off, Taylor looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge behind point. Two runs taken.
Down the leg side, helped through square leg for a couple.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Around middle and leg, tucked through mid-wicket for a single.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid on.
A length ball, around off, tucked through square leg for a run. HALF CENTURY FOR TAYLOR. One of his best knocks under pressure. He will aim to convert this into a century now.
Outside off, punched off the back foot back to the bowler.
Outside off, punched through the covers for a single.
Outside off, Nicholls looks to push but misses.
Around off, worked towards short mid-wicket.
Around middle, pushed towards mid on for a single.
Full and outside off, driven straight back to the bowler.
A short ball, pulled through mid-wicket for a couple.
Another long hop, pulled through mid-wicket for a single.
A short ball, on middle, pulled through backward square leg for a run.
Outside off, pushed towards gully where Kusal Mendis fumbles and concedes a single.

FOUR! That is a terrific shot. A half tracker, outside off, Taylor gets on top of the bounce and pulls it through mid-wicket. Akila Dananjaya tries to cut it off, puts in a despairing dive to his left but cannot even get to the ball.
Full and outside off, Taylor looks to drive but gets an outside edge to short third man. The fielder has a shy at the striker's end but misses. Replays show that had he hit, Taylor was a goner!
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
The batsman works it down the leg side. One run added to the total.
Outside off, punched through the covers for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Nicholls comes down the track and hits this back to the bowler.
Comes down the track again and bunts this towards long on for a run.
Full and outside off, Taylor gently laps this past the keeper towards fine leg for a couple.
Yorker around middle, swinging in, Nicholls looks to dig it out but ekes an inside edge towards square leg.
Dropped short, pulled through mid-wicket for a couple.
Full and around middle, flicked towards short mid-wicket.
Outside off, driven straight back to the bowler.
Full and around off, flicked through mid-wicket for a brace.
The batsman has punched that ball through the off side.
FOUR! Fractionally short, Nicholls goes back and drags this through mid-wicket. Kusal Perera gives it a chase from deep backward square leg and dives but in vain. 100-RUN STAND IS UP!

OUT! LBW! It is Akila again who has got a wicket. 4 out of 4! Full and around off, Nicholls looks to sweep but misses and is hit on the pads. Akila appeals and appeals and eventually umpire Illingworth raises his finger! Nicholls has a look at his partner and Taylor straightaway asks him to go for the review. Not of much use. No inside edge or glove, three reds and the 100-run stand is broken. Fantastic knock though.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
A short ball, pulled through mid-wicket for a single.
On middle and off, Taylor flicks it through square leg for a run.
Down the leg side, helped in front of leg slip. Played that with soft hands.
Outside off, dabbed to third man for a couple.
Full and outside off, driven straight to mid off.
On middle, flicked straight to short mid-wicket.
Full and outside off, driven through the covers for a couple.
The batsman has pushed it to the cover region. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Around off, solidly blocked out.
Landed outside off, spinning in, pushed through mid on for a single.

OUT! LBW! Oh that is a dead duck. A short ball, outside off, Watling rocks back to pull but the ball stays low and hits him on the pads. Akila runs towards the keeper in celebration and then appeals. The umpire raises his finger after a thought. Watling has a look at his partner, has a chat but then Taylor indicates not to take a review. Fair call. Crashing into the stumps. Would have exhausted their reviews. 4th 5-fer for Akila in Test cricket. TEA ON DAY 1!
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, watchfully blocked out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Defends this from the crease.
Full and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and outside off, Taylor comes down the track and drives it back to the bowler.
Pushes this through mid on for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Outside off, blocked solidly.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Outside off, pushed back defensively.
Full and outside off, driven towards mid off.
Full and outside off, swept through square leg for a single.
Outside off, watchfully blocked out.
Full and outside off, Santner drives this down the ground for a run.
Outside off, short in length, punched through the covers for a single.
Full and around off, watchfully pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Taylor comes down the track and drives it down the ground for a run.
Outside off, watchfully defended.
Around off, spinning in, Santner looks to tuck it to the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads.
FOUR! MAGNIFICENT! Full and outside off, Santner leans and drives this through the covers!
Full and outside off, Taylor looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge which flies behind point. Three runs taken.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On middle, pushed towards long on for a single.
Outside off, punched off the back foot for a run.
Full and around off, driven back to the bowler.
Outside off, punched off the back foot.
FOUR! Full and down the leg side, Taylor gets down and sweeps it behind square leg, beating the man at deep square leg to his right!
Outside off, punched off the back foot.
Full and down the leg side, swept through square leg for a single.
That ball has taken the inside edge of the batsman and thudded into his pads.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full and around off, watchfully defended.
Landed outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Full and around off, Taylor looks to flick but misses and the ball goes off his pads to short leg. The Lankans appeal for a catch but there is no bat involved.
The batsman works it down the leg side.
Around off, defended from the crease.
This one is down the leg side and the batsman leaves it alone.
Tossed up delivery on off, Santner strokes it towards long off and gets a single.
Flatter around off, Taylor defends it towards cover-point.
Flighted delivery on middle, Taylor comes down the track and blocks it off the front foot.
Once again Taylor comes down the track but this time he drives it back to the right of the bowler. Embuldeniya collects and Taylor rushes back inside his crease.

FOUR! Poor ball from Embuldeniya. He flights one down the leg side, Taylor gets down on one knee and sweeps it through the vacant backward square leg region for a boundary. 200 comes up for New Zealand with that.
Better this. Floated on off, RT defends it to get through the over.
Starts with a loopy delivery on off, Santner plants out his front foot and blocks it. Dickwella likes it as he shouts very well bowled to his colleague.
Floated on middle and leg. Santner defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off and middle, Santner looks to defend but it comes off the inside edge of his bat onto the pads.

First runs of the day. Short around off, Santner looks to cut but it goes off the thick outside edge of his bat, wide of slip. Due to heavy rains last night the outfield is relatively slow, So the ball does not get to the fence. Two taken by the batsmen.
Better line, tosses it up on the stumps, Santner blocks it.
Shorter on off, Santner punches it to mid off to get through the first over of the day unharmed.

OUT! What a start this is for Sri Lanka! Lakmal steams in and bowls a loose ball outside off. Taylor, facing his first ball of the day goes for the cut shot but ends up getting a fat outside edge to the right of the keeper.  Dickwella behind the stumps moves just a bit to his right and takes a simple catch. Dream start for the hosts, they wanted Taylor early and they have got just that.
Good length ball on the stumps, Southee does well to defend it off the front foot.
Southee is off the mark. Length ball outside off, Southee manages to guide it towards third man and gets to the other end.
Good length ball angling away. It is pitched outside off, Santner has no issues leaving it alone.
Closer to the off pole but Santner is aware of his stumps and lets it carry to the keeper.

Excellent delivery. Lakmal comes around the wicket and bowls it an away swinger pitching close to the off pole. Santner looks to defend but misses and luckily for him the ball does not kiss the outside edge.
Floated delivery on off, Southee looks to defend but gets a leading edge towards point which goes all along the ground..

This has spun a lot. Off spinner pitching outside off, Southee  gets on his back foot and looks to punch it to the off side but the ball spins in and hits him on the back leg wide away from the leg stump line.
Leg spinner now. Shorter around off, Southee punches it towards extra cover against the spin and gets a single.
Another beauty. Tossed up on off, the ball spins away from the southpaw. Santner looks to defend but misses.
Shorter on the stumps, MS defends it off the back foot.
Short and straight, Santner punches it straight back to the bowler.
Off the inside edge. Good length ball which comes in to the right-hander. Southee looks to defend but gets an inside edge which goes towards square leg allowing him to get to the bowler's end.
Good length ball outside off, Mitchell leaves it alone.
Hits the deck hard outside off, it comes in but Santner is aware of his off stump and offers a good leave.
Length ball on off, Santner defends it with a straight bat.
Lakmal tempts Santner to drive by bowling it outside off, Mitchell though is not interested and shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Santner lets it carry to the keeper.
Tossed up on off and middle, Tim defends it off the front foot.
Floated on middle, Southee strokes it towards mid on for one.

That excited the Sri Lankan players. Dananjaya flights it very full on middle and leg, Santner looks to defend but gets a big inside edge which goes towards the fine leg region. Two runs taken as the fielder cleans it up.
Floated on the stumps, MS blocks it properly this time.
Tossed up on middle, Santner nudges it towards long on for one.
Tossed up outside off, Southee plays it with soft hands towards third man and keeps the strike with a single.
Length ball on off, Southee stands tall and punches it through covers for a couple.
Fuller on off, Southee tucks it towards mid-wicket, he looks for a quick single but Santner shouts a loud no.
Length ball coming in with the angle, Southee defends it off the upper half of his bat with the angle.

Direct hit but safely in. Full on off, Southee drives it wide of mid off and takes a single. The fielder hits bull's eye at the bowler's end but Tim is in. The ball deflects off the stumps but does not cost any extra runs.

OUT! LBW! Second wicket for Lakmal today. His consistent line and lengths are finally reaping his benefits. Good length ball pitching outside off, Santner leaves it assuming it to swing away but the ball comes in with the angle and hits him flush on the front pad. Sri Lankan players put in a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Santner has a word with his partner, Southee and him opt against the review. Good decision as replays later on show that it would have been umpire's call as the ball was clipping the stumps enough to stay with the on-field call.
Outside off on a length, Somerville leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off, Southee defends it off the front foot.
Flighted on the stumps, Tim blocks it off the front foot.

SIX! First six of the gme and it has come off Southee's bat. Tossed up around middle, Southee says enough of the waiting game and he comes down the track. He gets to the pitch of the ball and smokes it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Tossed up on the stumps, Southee follows the maximum with a solid defense.
On the pads, Southee flicks it to mid-wicket.

OUT! Run out! What has happened here? Akila tosses one on leg, Southee looks to defend but the ball hits his front pad. Akila and the keeper go up in appeal but the umpire says nothing doing. But in the meantime, the ball goes towards gully and Tim had come halfway down looking for a single. Somerville, initially was calling for a run but then turns his back on his partner. Tim is in no man's land. Dhananjaya de Silva throws it at the keeper's end and Dickwella does the rest. Terrible day for New Zealand so far.
Good length ball on off, Somerville pushes it wide of cover and gets a single.
Length ball outside off, Boult looks to play it initially but then leaves it in the end in typical tailender's style.

DROPPED! Tough chance but still a chance. Good length ball on off, Boult looks to drive it on the up but does so uppishly. Lakmal gets his right hand on it in his follow up but cannot stick it in. The ball goes behind the stumps at the bowler's end and Boult rather than getting out ends up getting a single.
Bouncer! Somerville sways away from it.
On the stumps, Somerville defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball outside off, William looks to defend but misses.
Tossed up on off, TB defends it off the front foot.
Floated on the stumps, Boult defends it.
Tossed up on off and middle, Boult looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge towards point.
Shorter on off, Boult defends it off his back foot this time.
Tossed up on middle, Boult comes down the track and strokes it back towards the bowler.
Floated on the stumps, Trent defends it to get through the over.

EDGED AND FOUR! Fuller ball outside off, Somerville looks to drive but ends up getting a fat outside edge. It flies wide of the diving gully fielder and to the fence at third man for a boundary. Bonus yet vital runs these for New Zealand.
Follows the edgy boundary with a solid front foot defense.
Length ball on off, WS punches it wide of cover for one.
Fuller on middle, Boult strokes it wide of mid on for one.
Length ball outside off, Somerville drives it wide of sweeper cover and gets a couple as the fielder cleans it up.
Good length ball around off, WS defends it towards cover to get through the over.
Tossed up around off, Boult comes down the track and milks it towards long on with the spin for a single.
Floated on off, Somerville bends his back and defends it.
Shorter on middle and leg, Somerville tucks it wide of short leg.
Shorter on off, WS defends it off the back foot.

NOT OUT! Brilliant review from Somerville. He survives to fight another day. Loopy off spinner pitching outside off, Somerville looks to defend. The ball lobs off his pad and goes straight into the hands of short leg. Sri Lanka players put in an appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Somerville takes the review. Snicko shows there was no bat or glove involved. Ball Tracker then rolls in and shows that though the impact was umpire's call, the ball was going on to miss the stumps.
Floated on off, WS defends it off the front foot.
Starts with a flighted delivery on off, Boult strokes it towards cover for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Somerville blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted outside off, Somerville looks to drive but misses.
Tossed up on the stumps, WS keeps it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Slower through the air outside off, Somerville looks to drive but misses.
FOUR! Bonus runs for New Zealand, frustrating for Sri Lanka. Tossed up on off, Boult comes down the track and swivels it with the spin over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up on off, Boult blocks it off the front foot.
Floated on middle and leg, Boult defends it in a proper number 10 fashion.

Miscommunication but safe. Tossed up on off, Boult defends it with soft hands. The ball goes towards point, Somerville calls for a run, Boult says no but still goes with it. Luckily Somerville gets in.
Tossed up outside off, WS looks to defend inside the line but misses.
Tossed up outside off, Somerville comes down the track and looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.

This is comical. Tossed up outside off, Boult looks play the paddle but gets a leading edge on it. The ball goes through the grill and gets stuck in. Boult moves away from all the surrounding fielders. After a while, Boult lets the keeper take it off. Not out though as the ball was dead.
Floated on the stumps, Boult defends it off the front foot.
SIX! Boult is enjoying his time out in the middle. Tossed up on off, Boult comes down the track and lofts it over long off for a maximum.
Floated on off, Boult comes down the track and nudges it towards cover for one.
Flighted on the stumps, WS keeps it out.
On the stumps, blocked by Somerville.
Tossed up on off, Boult comes down the track and nudges it to long on for one.
On the pads, Somerville flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Spinning away and it is wide of leg stump. William looks to flick but misses.
Floated on off, Somerville plays it towards point and once again there is yes and no between the batsmen but misfield  at point allows them to take a single.
Floated on middle and leg, Boult looks to defend but gets an inside edge towards the square leg region allowing them to take a single.
Shorter on off, Somerville defends it off the back foot to get through another over unharmed.

OUT! Caught! Lakmal strikes in his very first over of his new spell. His third of the day and New Zealand lose their 9th. Trent Boult's entertaining cameo comes to an end. Good length ball on off, Boult looks to loft it over mid on but does not get the elevation and he ends up hitting it straight to Kusal Perera at mid on.

OUT! LBW! Unsuccessful review. Full ball outside off, Ajaz looks to play it across the line and gets hit on the pads. Huge appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger. Ajaz Patel takes the review, replay rolls in and shows that the ball was clipping the leg pole. NEW ZEALAND BOWLED OUT FOR 249.
Wild swing first up. Good length ball on the fourth stump line, the ball swings away and goes towards the first slip. Watling does really well as he dives to his left to collect the ball.
No wild swing on this one. It is a good length ball around off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Karunaratne pushes it to cover.
Fuller on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
On off, Karunaratne defends it with authority.
On the fourth stump, Dimuth leaves it alone to get through the first over without any damage.
Good length ball on the off stump, Thirimanne drives it down the ground and gets off the mark with a couple.
Shorter in length this time, Thirimanne defends it off the back foot.
Fuller in length this time but on the pads, Lahiru flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Another full length delivery on the middle pole, Dimuth defends it towards the off side.
FOUR! Excellent shot from Karunaratne! It was a full delivery on the pads. Dimuth flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for the first boundary of the innings.
Beaten! Shorter delivery outside the off stump, Karunaratne looks to defend but misses the ball.
Good length ball outside off, Thirimanne taps it towards gully.
Bouncer! Thirimanne ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on off, Thirimanne defends it off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, Thirimanne shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball close to off stump, Lahiru defends it off the front foot.
Length ball on off, Thirimanne tucks it to the on side.
Full delivery on the middle pole, Dimuth tries to flick it towards the leg side but gets a thick edge towards the off side.
Good length ball on the off pole, Karunaratne defends it to the off side.
Another one on a good length outside off stump, DK defends it again towards cover.
Fuller in length this time on the off stump, Karunaratne pushes it towards mid off.
Full delivery outside off stump, Dimuth prods forward and pushes it to mid off and takes off for a single.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Southee. It was on a good length on the off pole. Lahiru prods forward to defend but is not able to put any bat on it.
Good length ball outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
OHH! Full outside off, Karunaratne looks to drive it on the up but misses.
On the pads, Karunaratne flicks it towards square leg for a couple.
Boult misses his line and bowls one down the leg side. Karunaratne looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off stump, Thirimanne leaves it alone.
Another good length delivery on the off stump, Thirimanne defends it to the off side. The batter wants to take a single but it is not there as the fielder at point makes a diving stop.
Good length ball on middle pole, Thirimanne drives it back to the bowler.
Back of a length delivery outside the off stump, Lahiru lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on the middle pole angling in to the left hander, Thirimanne flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Full delivery on the off pole, Dimuth pushes it towards mid off.
Boult steams in and hits the deck hard around off, it comes in slightly but Thirimanne offers a classical leave to it.
Good length ball on off, Thirimanne defends it towards cover-point.
Bouncer! It is on middle and leg, Lahiru sits under it and the ball goes just past him.
Full on off and middle, Lahiru nudges it to mid on.
FOUR! Excellent shot! First boundary of the day for Thirimanne. Good length ball around off, Lahiru leans back and cuts it through point for a boundary.
In the air but safe! Fuller on middle and leg, Thirimanne flicks it uppishly but luckily it falls well short of short mid-wicket.
Starts with a loopy delivery outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Flighted on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Floated on off, DK blocks it off his front foot.
Quicker and shorter on off, Karunaratne taps it towards gully.
Shorter on off, Karunaratne drives it through point for a couple.
FOUR! No power just placement. Short and wide outside off, Karunaratne waits and then places it fine towards the third man region for a boundary.
Short ball on middle, Thirimanne rocks back and defends it towards mid on.
On a good length on the middle pole, Thirimanne pushes it back to the bowler.
Full delivery outside the off stump, Thirimanne drives it towards cover. No run.
Good length ball on middle pole, Lahiru blocks it out to mid on.
On a good length delivery on the pads, Lahiru flicks it off his pads and crosses over for a single.
Short delivery outside the off stump, Dimuth cuts hard but straight to the point fielder. DK will feel that he missed out there as it was a ball to be hit.
Loopy delivery outside off, Thirimanne drives it but straight to cover. Lahiru will be gutted to miss out on that one.
Very full on the pads, LT defends it back to the bowler.
Sharp spin on this one. Floated on middle and leg, Thirimanne does well to read the spin and block it.
Tossed up on middle, Thirimanne strokes it to mid on.
Shorter on off, Lahiru blocks it off the back foot.
Maiden for Somerville. Better over this. The last ball is flighted on off, Lahiru blocks it.
Starts with a short ball on top of off, Karunaratne punches it through point and gets three as the fielder cleans it before the ropes.
Flighted on middle, Thirimanne defends it off the front foot.
Short around off, Thirimanne looks to cut but the ball goes off the lower half of his bat towards point for one.
On the pads, Dimuth comes down the track and flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Floated outside off, Thirimanne leaves it alone.

OUT! Stumped! New Zealand needed a wicket before lunch and Ajaz Patel has given them just that in his first over. Not a smart choice from Thirimanne. Ajaz flights one outside off, it is slower through the air. Lahiru comes down the track and looks to play it on the leg side. He misreads the spin and it cuts the bat and body on its way to the keeper. Watling takes the bails off as Lahiru is too far in front.
Shorter on off, Karunaratne runs it down towards third man and gets a couple.

DROPPED! Taylor is the culprit! Somerville will feel hard done by this. William tosses it up outside off, Karunaratne goes for the drive but ends up getting a thick outside edge. The ball flies to the right of first slip. Taylor misreads and the ball hits his right hand and lobs behind for a couple.
Floated on the stumps, DK defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle and off, Karunaratne blocks it off his front foot.
Ohh! Floated on the pads, Karunaratne flicks it uppishly just wide of short leg.
Tossed up on middle, Karunarate comes down the track and nudges it wide of mid on for one.
Tossed up around off, Karunaratne comes down the track and blocks it.
Short around off, Karunaratne looks to cut but misses.

Ajaz once again tries to bowl it on the rough which is developing outside off stump of the left-hander. Karunaratne looks to negate it by coming down the track. He misses his flick and the ball hits him on the pads. There is a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Shorter around off, DK runs it down to third man for one.
Floated on off, Mendis defends it by getting right behind the ball.
Short on off, Mendis punches it towards point and gets a single. LUNCH ON DAY 2!
FOUR! What a glorious way to start the session. Tossed up outside off, Mendis gets on his front foot and drives it through mid off for a boundary!
Now calmly leaves this one which is outside off.
Floated outside off, Mendis leaves it alone.
Short on off, Kusal plays the nataraja pull shot but straight to mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Mendis blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Kusal drives it straight to the bowler.
Flighted on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, Karunaratne flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Shorter on off and middle, Mendis defends it off the upper half of his bat.
Beauty! Tossed up on off, Mendis looks to defend but the ball spins away and squares Kusal all ends up.
Floated on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.

EDGED AND FOUR! Taylor once again is lethargic at slip. Short around off, Mendis looks to cut but gets a thick outside edge which goes just left of Taylor at first slip and to the fence for a boundary.
Flighted on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Crisp! Flighted on off, Karunaratne lunges out and drives it with sweet timing straight down the ground for a boundary.
Follows it up with a gentle front foot defense.
Tossed up on the stumps, DK keeps it out.
Flights one on off, Dimuth strokes it to mid off.
Arm ball on off, Karunaratne taps it wide of gully and keeps the strike.
Flighted on off, Dimuth defends it with a straight bat.
Shorter on middle, Karunaratne flicks it against the spin towards the fine leg region. Santner gives it a chase and pulls it before the ropes. Two taken.
Floated on middle and off, Karunaratne strokes it to mid on and gets to the other end.
Flighted on off, Mendis blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Short on middle, Mendis gets on his back foot and pulls it over the vacant mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Short again but this is on off, Kusal defends it towards point.
Flighted and spinning away from outside off, Dimuth guides it with the spin towards gully.
Short and wide outside off, Karunaratne punches it with the spin towards cover.
Very full on off, DK nudges it to mid on.
Flighted outside off, Dimuth leaves it alone.

UPPISH AND FOUR! Somerville tosses it up around off, Karunaratne drives it uppishly to the right of Somerville. The tall spinner puts in a good dive but can just get a finger tip to it. That is not enough to take the pace of the ball as it still goes to the long off fence.
Floated on middle, Karunaratne flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, KM defends it off the front foot.
Floated on the stumps, Mendis keeps it out.
Flighted on off, Mendis drives it straight to cover.
Floated on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Kusal has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Shorter on off, Mendis defends it off the back foot.
Flighted around off, Karunaratne defends it towards point.
Edged but short! Flighted outside off, Karunaratne looks to drive but gets an outside edge. This time it does not carry to Rosco and he does well to stop it with a dive.
Shorter on off, Karunaratne plays it to point.
Loopy ball on middle, Karunaratne taps it back to the bowler.
Flighted on off, Dimuth blocks it away.
Slower through the air on off, Karunaratne defends it to get through the over.
Uppish but safe! Tossed up around middle, Mendis comes down the track and drives it uppishly towards extra cover. Luckily for him, it falls short of the fielder.
Floated on the stumps, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Flighted on the stumps, Mendis gets on his front foot and blocks it.
On off, Mendis keeps it out with a classical front foot defense.
FOUR! Swept and swept fine. Floated on the pads, Mendis gets down on one knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary.
Driven towards the mid-off by Mendis.
Tossed up on off, Karunaratne pushes it to cover.
Sharp turn! Floated around off, Karunaratne looks to defend but gets beaten.
Flights one on the stumps, Karunaratne defends it with a straight bat.
Shorter on off, Karunaratne punches it to cover.
On the pads, DK flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
On the stumps, Mendis keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle and off, Karunaratne comes down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Short and spinning in, Karunaratne plays it late and wide of slip and third man. Raval at third man mops it up before the ropes. Two taken.
Shorter on off, DK blocks it off the back foot.
Flatter on the pads, Karunaratne looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.

OUT! LBW! The Sri Lankan skipper is out of here. Ajaz bowls one quicker on middle and off, Dimuth looks to flick but misses. The Kiwis ask the question and the umpire gives Karunaratne his marching orders by raising his finger. Karunaratne and Mendis have a word and they opt against the review. Good decision as replay later on shows that the ball would have gone onto hit the leg pole.
Flighted outside off, Mathews starts his innings with a leave.
Quick and spinning in. It is on the leg side, Mendis looks to play it to the on side but misses.
FOUR! Hammered away. Somerville is guilty of bowling it too short, Mendis picks it early and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
On the pads, Mendis flicks it to the on side for one.
Mathews is off the mark. Off spinner on the pads, Mathews glances it with the spin towards fine leg for a single.
Quicker and shorter on middle and leg, Kusal tucks it down and wide of short leg.
SIX! Mendis won't miss out on those hit me balls. Tossed up on middle and leg, it is overpitched by Somerville. Kusal gets down on one knee and sweeps it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie.
Arm ball outside off, Mathews leaves it alone.
In the air but short. Short outside off, Mathews looks to cut but does so uppishly but it falls short of Santner at backward point.
Tossed up on off, Mathews keeps it out.
FOUR! This time Mathews cuts it with authority! Short and wide outside off, Mathews gets on his back foot and cuts it right off the meat through point for a boundary.
Once again Ajaz bowls short, Mathews punches it to cover
On the pads, AM flicks it to square leg.
Starts right on the money. Flighted on off, there is late spin on this one. Mendis looks to defend but it goes off the outer half of his bat towards the third man region for a single.
Shorter on off and middle, Mathews gets right behind it and defends it back towards the bowler.
On middle and leg, Mathews tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter on off, Mathews defends it towards cover.
Tossed up on off, Angelo blocks it. Though Santner has been right on the money he has not got too much spin here.
Now he induces spin here. Floated on off, Mathews looks to defend with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge which goes towards the third man region for a single.
Shorter on top of middle, Mathews gets on his back foot and punches it to mid on.
Beauty! Slower through the air on off, Mathews looks to defend it off his back foot but gets beaten by the spin on that one.
Now a confident defense. Tossed up on off, Mathews keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Angelo flicks it to square leg.
Short around off, Mathews cuts but cannot get it past the man at point.
Floated on the stumps, AM defends it off the front foot.

Not Out! There was no bat involved but the impact was outside leg. New Zealand lose one of their two reviews. Tossed up on leg, Mendis looks to flick but misses. The ball hits him on the pads. There is a huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Williamson after a few consultation takes the review. Replay rolls in, Ultra Edge shows no involvement of bat but the Ball Tracker shows that the impact was outside leg.
Floated on off, Mendis pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up on the stumps, KM blocks it.
FOUR! Short and punished. It is on middle, Kusal picks the length early and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Short again this is on off, KM punches it to cover.
On the pads, Mendis flicks it to the man at mid-wicket.
Floated on the stumps, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
On the stumps, Mathews keeps it out.
Short and around off, Angelo cuts it but finds point.
Once again cuts but finds point.
Floated on the stumps, Angelo defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, AM keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Kusal defends it off the front foot.
Short around off, Mendis punches it towards cover and gets a single.
Flighted on off, Angelo defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Mathews strokes it to cover.
Floated on off, Mathews defends it with a straight bat.
On off, Mathews blocks it to get through the over.
Flatter on off, Kusal defends it off the front foot.
Shorter around off, Mendis cuts it through point and gets a couple as Santner goes after it from point and pulls it before the ropes.
Short around off, Mendis runs it down to third man and gets a single.
Floated on off, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Short on off, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
On the stumps, AM blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Mendis defends it calmly.
Slightly shorter on middle, Mendis keeps his eyes on the ball and defends it.
Floated on off, Mendis blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up on the stumps, Kusal blocks it off the front foot.
On the pads, KM turns it to the on side and gets a single.
Floated on off, AM keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off, Mendis leaves it alone.
No swing on this one. It is outside off, KM shoulders arms to this.
Length ball on off, Kusal blocks it off.
On the fourth stump line, Mendis has no business with it.
Closer to off pole, Kusal defends it to cover.
Same line and this one is defended towards mid on. Maiden for Southee on his return.
Slower and shorter outside off, Mathews punches it towards cover for a single.
Floated on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Shorter around off, Kusal taps it towards third man for a couple.
Floated on off, KM blocks it.
Slower through the air on off, Mendis defends it off the inner half of his bat.
Floated on the stumps, Mendis blocks it away.
Southee bowls the effort ball and bangs it in short. Mathews sways away from it.
Good length ball outside off, Mathews leaves it alone.
Almost chopped on! Good length ball around off, Mathews is late in getting his bat down. The ball hits the bottom half of his bat and onto the pads. It goes past the stumps and to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on middle, Angelo strokes it to mid on.
Fuller on middle, AM keeps it out.
Tossed up on middle, Mendis comes down the track and taps the ball onto the ground.
Shorter on off, Mendis punches it to cover.
Floated on the stumps, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
On the stumps, AM blocks it off the front foot.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Once again short, Mathews cannot get it past point.
Good length ball on off, Mathews blocks it off the front foot.
FOUR! 100 comes up for Sri Lanka in style. Good length ball around off, Mathews cuts it with venom through point for a boundary. Much needed as this has come after almost 9 overs.
On the pads, Mathews flicks it to mid-wicket.
FOUR! Poor bowling this from Southee. He strays one down the leg side, Angelo flicks it fine down the leg side to score the second boundary of the over.
Length ball on off, Mathews defends it calmly.
Fuller on off, Mathews drives it to mid on off the inner half of his bat. End of an expensive over, 8 from it.
Floated on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, Mendis turns it towards mid-wicket for one.
IN THE AIR AND SIX! Tossed up on off, Mathews frees his arms and lofts it over long off for a biggie. It looked like he did not connect well but he had got enough meat on it.
Floated on the stumps, Santner defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on the stumps, AM keeps it out.
Angelo has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Fuller on off, Mendis keeps it out.
Outside off, asking the batsman to drive but Mendis says not now mate.
Full on off, Kusal pushes it to mid on.
Full ball outside off, Kusal defends it towards cover.
Once again bowls it full around off, Mendis keeps it out.
Good length ball outside off, Kusal shoulders arms to it.
On the pads, Mathews turns it to the on side.
Floated on middle and off, Mathews keeps it out.
FOUR! Runs starting to come quicker now. Shorter around off. Mathews cuts it through point for a boundary. Also brings up the 50-run stand between the duo.
Floats it on off, Angelo defends it off the front foot.
Floated on the stumps, Mathews blocks it away.
On the pads, Angelo flicks it to the on side.
Good length ball on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Outside off, Kusal leaves it alone.
On the fourth stump line, Mendis leaves it alone.
On the body, Mendis glances it towards fine leg for one.
Inside edge to the rescue. Very full and inswinging ball on off, Mathews looks to defend but luckily the ball kisses the inside edge and goes onto the pads.
On the pads, Mathews flicks it but finds mid-wicket.
Short ball on middle and leg, Mendis pulls it towards deep square leg and gets a couple.
On the pads, Kusal turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Floated on middle and leg, Mathews turns it to the on side and gets a single.
Tossed up on the pads, Mathews turns it to fine leg and rotates the strike.
Loopy delivery on off, Angleo blocks it.
FOUR! Mathews shows aggression once again. Tossed up on middle and off, Angelo comes down the track and squeezes it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Mendis plays it to point.
This time gets it wide of the man at point for a single.
Good length ball on off, Angelo defends it off the front foot.
Gets behind this length ball and solidly blocks it.
On the pads, Angelo flicks it to the on side for a single. Trail now stands at 120.
Length ball on off, KM keeps it out.
Quicker on middle and off, Mathews tucks it to short leg.
On the pads, Angelo turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
On the pads, Mendis turns it to the on side.
Shorter on off, Mendis pulls it towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR! This duo continue to trouble New Zealand. Tossed up on middle, Mathews comes down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
On the pads, Mathews flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Mathews pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on off, Angelo blocks it off the front foot.
Shorter around off, Mathews punches it to point.
Floated on the stumps, Angelo defends it off the front foot.
Shorter on off, Mathews taps it towards third man and gets to the other end.
Flights one on off, Mendis defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Mathews defends it towards mid off.
Length ball outside off, Angelo leaves it alone.
Once again outside Mathews offers no stroke to this one.
Length ball on the stumps, Mathews blocks it.
On the pads, Mathews nudges it towards mid-wicket for a couple.
Outside off and it is left alone once again by Angelo.
Tossed up on the stumps, Mendis keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Angelo punches it to cover.
Short again on off, Mendis plays it to point.

FOUR! Fifty for Mendis. This has been a fine knock from the young man. He will now look to convert this into a big one. He gets a gift to get to his 10th Test fifty. A low full toss on the pads, Mendis flicks it fine down the leg side for a boundary.

OUT! Caught! Fifty and out! Mendis will be gutted with himself. He was looking so good out in the middle but has thrown it away. This has been a trademark of his career. Tossed up on middle, Mendis looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies to the man at slip, and guess who takes the catch? Yes, it is Ross Taylor. The 77-run stand is broken and that will be Tea on Day 2.
Perera is off the mark straightaway!  Tossed up on middle, Perera comes down the track and flicks it wide of mid on for a single.

Almost a calamity there. Good length ball on off, Perera strokes it wide of mid off and calls for a run. Mathews though was not interested and sends him back. Watling has a shy at the bowler's end but misses.
Good length delivery on the leg stump, Perera defends it off his back foot towards mid on.

OUT! Caught! New Zealand wanted to attack the new man and they have done just that. Short ball around off, Perera was in two minds whether to leave it or play the shot. He goes for the latter but half-heartedly. He just ends up lobbing it straight to Mitchell Santner at cover-point. New Zealand once again get their noses just in front.
Back of a length delivery  on the middle stump, Dhananjaya defends it off the back foot.
Boult bowls a fuller length delivery outside off, de Silva pushes it to mid off.
Another back of a length delivery, Dhananjaya flicks it towards square leg. Excellent over from Boult. A wicket and no runs in it.
On the pads, Mathews flicks it towards square leg for one.
Floated on off, de Silva blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Dhananjaya keeps it out.

FOUR! But a good effort in the field from Santner. Short and wide outside off, Dhananjaya cuts it through point. Santner chases it from point and looks to pull it back before the ropes but his hand ends up touching the ropes.
Floated on the stumps, de Silva keeps it out.
On the stumps, de Silva defends it.
Back of a length delivery aimed at the body, Mathews flicks it towards square leg and takes a single. The trail now is under 100.
Good length delivery on the middle pole, Dhananjaya defends it towards cover.
On a good length on middle, de Silva defends it off his back foot.
Shorter in length this time, Dhananjaya rocks back and pushes it towards the point fielder.
Good length delivery on the pads, de Silva flicks it towards square leg.
Good length delivery on the middle stump, DdS blocks it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Mathews pushes it back to the bowler.
Tossed up around off, Angelo defends it to cover.
Tossed up on the stumps, AM keeps it out.
Short and quick outside off, Mathews looks to cut but misses.
FOUR! Mathews continues his good work. Tossed up on middle, Angelo comes down the track and lofts it over mid on for a boundary.
Short around off, Mathews punches it to cover.
Good length delivery on middle, de Silva defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length delivery on middle stump, de Silva flicks it towards square leg. No run.
Another back of a length delivery on the body, de Silva flicks it to mid-wicket. Another dot ball.
Boult keeps on bowling back of a length. This time Dhananjaya flicks it square leg for a single.
Good length delivery outside off stump, de Silva defends it towards the cover fielder.
On a good length delivery outside off stump, Dhananjaya leaves it alone.
Full and around off, Dhananjaya comes down the track and looks to swing but the ball goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.

OUT! Terrific return catch! Sri Lanka have now lost a wicket either side of Tea. Poor shot from de Silva. Tossed up outside off, Dhananjaya comes down the track and looks to go big but is not quite to the pitch of the ball. Hits it back to Ajaz Patel who reacts well to take a sharp catch. New Zealand still in  shout for a decent first innings lead. Sri Lanka still behind by 94.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Dickwella defends it to cover.
Another loopy delivery on the middle stump, Niroshan sweeps it fine but straight to the fine leg fielder.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Dickwella prods forward to defend but gets hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but  the umpire is unmoved.
Another flighted delivery on the off stump, Dickwella blocks it out towards cover.
Shorter around off, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Shorter on off, Mathews looks to cut but gets a thick outside edge whcih flies wide of the man at slip towards third man. Two runs taken.
Loopy delivery on the middle stump, Mathews flicks it towards mid-wicket.

Fifty for Angelo Mathews! His 34th Test fifty for Mathews. This has been a fine knock from the experienced campaigner. He gets to his fifty with a flick towards mid-wicket for a single. He raises his bat in appreciation. He will look to convert this into a big one.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Dickwella looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is a loud LBW appeal but not given by the umpire.
Loopy delivery outside the off stump, Dickwella lets it go to the keeper.

OUT! Caught! Another Sri Lankan batsman who does not hang around a lot after getting to his half ton. 5-wicket haul for Ajaz Patel. Quicker on off, Mathews looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge and it goes straight to Taylor at first slip. Sri Lanka in trouble now as they still trail by 91.
Flighted on off, Akila starts his innings with a front foot defense.
Floated on the stumps, AD blocks it away.
Floated on off, Akila taps it back to the bowler.
On the pads, AK flicks it to mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Akila pushes it to cover.
Full delivery on the middle stump, Dickwella paddles sweeps it to fine leg for a brace.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Dickwella plays it towards mid off for a quick single.
Beaten!  Flighted delivery outside off stump, Dananjaya tries to defend it but gets deceived in the air.
Another brilliant delivery from Somerville, Akila in another attempt to defend it misses the ball completely.

OUT! Caught! Another one bites the dust! First wicket for Somerville in this game. The consistent line and length he has bowled in this over has bore its fruit. Floated outside off, Akila goes for a big drive but gets a thick outside edge which goes straight into the hands of Ross Taylor at first slip. From 144/3 they are now reeling at 161/7.
Loopy delivery on the pads, Lakmal tries to defend but gets hit on the pads and goes to short leg fielder. The Kiwi fielders appeal for a possible bat and pad decision but the umpire is unmoved.
Tossed up around off, Niroshan defends it off the front foot. The ball goes towards point and they take a single.
On middle, Lakmal pushes it to mid on.
Appeal but nothing from the umpire. Floated on leg, Lakmal looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. There is a huge appeal but nothing from the umpire as the ball seemed to be going down leg side.
SIX! This one is out of here. Tossed up on off, Lakmal gets down on one knee and hammers his slog sweep over the mid-wicket fence for a maximum.
Follows it up with a calm defense.
Shorter on off, Lakmal punches it to cover.
Tossed up on the stumps, Dickwella defends it with straight bat.
Flighted delivery on the pads, Niroshan plays another paddle sweep towards fine leg but this time it is only a single.
Loopy delivery on the off pole, Suranga prods forward and flicks it towards long on for a single.
Flatter delivery on the off stump, Dickwella defends it to point and takes of for a single but is sent back by Lakmal.
Another flat delivery on the off pole, Dickwella blocks it out towards the off side.
Loopy delivery on the middle stump, ND looks to defend but gets hit on the pads and the bolwers make a stifled appeal for LBW but is turned down.
Tossed up on middle, Lakmal pushes it back to the bowler.
Floated on off, the ball keeps low but Lakmal does well to keep it out.
Flighted on the stumps, SL defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, Lakmal flicks it wide of mid-wicket for a couple.
Outside off, Lakmal leaves it alone.
Flighted outside off, Lakmal looks to defend but gets beaten by the spin.
Tossed up outside off, Dickwella goes for an ambitious reverse sweep but does not connect.
Floated on off and middle, Niroshan keeps it out.
Loopy delivery outside the off stump, Dickwella sweeps from off stump towards deep mid-wicket and calls Lakmal for a single.

NOT OUT! Very good review from Lakmal. There is no bat and the ball is going on to miss the leg pole. Flighted on off, Lakmal looks to defend but the ball goes through and lobs off his pad towards first slip. The Kiwi players ask the question and the umpire raises his finger. Lakmal after a few thoughts takes the review. Replays roll in, first up, the Ultra Edge shows no involvement of either bat or glove. Ball Tracker then follows and shows that the ball was going on to miss the leg pole.
Flighted delivery bowled at middle stump, Lakmal flicks it towards fine leg and the batters take a single.
Loopy delivery on the off pole, Niroshan pushes it towards mid off and takes a single. Dickwella will keep strike for the next over.
Floated outside off, Dickwella reverse sweeps it towards backward point for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Lakmal pushes it to mid on for a run.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Dickwella comes down the track and looks to defend but the ball hits him on his pad. There is a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Loopy ball outside off, Dickwella looks to sweep but gets hit on the pad. Appeal follows but the umpire is unmoved and rightfully so as the impact was outside off.
First extra of the game. On the pads, Dickwella looks to flick but the ball goes off his thigh pad down the leg side for a single.
On the stumps, Suranga blocks it out.
Tossed up outside off, Dickwella looks to drive but misses.
Flighted on off, Dickwella sweeps it to deep mid-wicket for one.
On the stumps, Lakmal blocks it off the front foot.
Off spinner outside off, Lakmal looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Short around off, Lakmal cuts it towards point for a single.
Flighted on off, Dickwella reverse sweeps it to point.
Flighted on the stumps, Lakmal blocks it off the front foot.
On the pads, Lakmal flicks it to the on side for a single.
Flighted on off, Dickwella comes down the track and taps it back to the bowler.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On the stumps, ND keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Dickwella taps it back to Ajaz.
Looped up ball on off, Lakmal defends it with calmness.
Flighted on middle, Lakmal pushes it back to the bowler.
FOUR! Lakmal is going after selected ones here. Tossed up on off, Suranga comes down the track and lofts it over covers for a boundary.
Follows it up with a sensible front foot defense.
On the pads, Lakmal keeps it out.
FOUR! Excellent shot this time from Lakmal. It was another loopy delivery from Somerville. Lakmal like a proper top order batsman prods forward and drives it straight past the bowler for a boundary.
Sweeps it away wide of square leg for a couple.
Tossed up on off, Lakmal nudges it wide of mid off for one.
On the stumps, Lakmal defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, Lakmal looks to drive but misses.
On off, Suranga pushes it to cover.
Short around off, Lakmal cuts it to point.
Loopy delivery on the middle pole, Dickwella sweeps but straight to fine leg.
Flighted delivery on middle, Niroshan flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Another loopy delivery on middle, Lakmal blocks it back to the bowler.

DROPPED! Latham is the culprit here. It was a shorter delivery on the leg stump, Lakmal tries to flick it away but goes to Latham at short leg who is unable to hold on to it. It was a difficult chance.
Loopy delivery on off stump, Lakmal defends it back to the bowler.
Short delivery outside off stump, Lakmal rocks back and punches it towards cover.
Flighted on the stumps, Dickwella keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Niroshan taps it towards third man and gets a couple.
Tossed up outside off, ND lunges out and defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, Dickwella drags it towards backward square leg for one.
Tossed up on off, Lakmal nudges it to mid off.
On the stumps, Lakmal blocks it out to get through the over.
Floated outside off, Dickwella looks to drive but misses.
Shorter on off and middle, Niroshan punches it towards mid on for a single.
On the pads, Lakmal looks to defend but gets hit on thigh pad.
