On middle, Lakmal strokes it wide of mid on for one.

Comical fielding from Ajaz! Tossed up on off, Dickwella plays the reverse sweep to wrads the left of backward point. Ajaz Patel thinks the ball will come to him but then he sees that the ball will go past him so he puts a very funny looking dive. In the end, he saves a run.
Outside off, Niroshan leaves it alone.
Flighted on off, Lakmal defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, Lakmal leaves it alone.
Floated outside off, Suranga looks to drive but gets squared up.

Lakmal goes hard at this tossed up delivery outside off. It finds the outside edge and goes wide of slip. They take a couple but hang on Lakmal keeps his bat on the line meaning it is a run short. So just a single.
Floated on the stumps, SL blocks it out.
On the stumps, Niroshan defends it to get through the over.
Tossed up on off, Dickwella sweeps it to backward square leg and looks for a single but Lakmal says no.
Floated on the stumps, ND defends it sensibly.
On the pads, Dickwella turns it to the on side and gets a single. Brings up the 200 for Sri Lanka. The deficit now is 49.
On the pads, Lakmal looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
On off, Lakmal keeps it out.
Defends it calmly to get through the over.
Tossed up outside off, Dickwella reverse sweeps it towards backward point and gets a single.
Arm ball outside off, Lakmal leaves it alone.
Floated outside off, Suranga looks to drive but gets beaten.
Outside off, Suranga shoulders arms to it.
On the stumps, Lakmal keeps it out.
Outside off and Lakmal does not tease that one.
Good length delivery outside off stump, Dickwella drives it through point region for a brace. The fielder at third man runs in and makes a diving stop.
Back of a length delivery on the middle stump, Dickwella flicks it to the on side.
On a good length on off stump, Dickwella drives it towards cover for another brace.
This time a short delivery which goes over the head of Dickwella. The batsman tries to play the uppercut but misses.
Good length delivery outside off stump, Dickwella guides it uppishly towards third man and takes a single.
On a good length delivery, Lakmal defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up outside off, Dickwella once again brings out the reverse sweep and hits it to third man for one.
Outside off, Lakmal leaves it alone.
On off, Lakmal strokes it to mid off for a single.
Tossed up on off, Dickwella comes down the track and blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Dickwella sweeps it to square leg for a single to take the partnership to 48.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Good length delivery on the middle stump, Dickwella defends it towards the mid-wicket.
Back of a length delivery outside the off stump, Dickwella rocks back and blocks it out.
On a good length this time on middle stump, Dickwella pushes it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Excellent batting from Dickwella. It was a short delivery from Boult which was going over ND's head but Dickwella had other ideas. The batter just uppercuts the ball over the keeper's head for a boundary. With that boundary, the fifty run partnership comes up between the two.
WIDE! Another short delivery from Boult but this time it is way over the batsman's head and it has been wided.
Full toss on middle, Dickwella strokes it to mid on.
Short ball, Dickwella looks to pull but misses.
Slower through the air outside off, Lakmal looks to defend but gets beaten.
Floated on the stumps, SL defends it with confidence.
Floats one on off, Lakmal defends it with calmness.
Outside off, Lakmal does not tease that one.
Once again Lakmal has nothing to do with the ball outside off.
Tossed up on off, Lakmal bends forward and blocks it to get through the over.
Floated on off, Dickwella drives it but straight to cover.
Tossed up around off, Dickwella sweeps it through mid-wicket. Santner gives it a chase and cleans it up before the ropes. Two taken.
Flighted on off, ND blocks it.
On off, Dickwella drags his sweep to square leg for one.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
On the stumps, Lakmal blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter delivery on middle stump, Dickwella plays another sweep towards mid-wicket and cross over for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Lakmal comes down the track and pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Another loopy delivery on the middle, Dickwella comes down the track and flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on the middle pole, Niroshan goes for another sweep but this time towards fine leg and take another single.
Outside off, Lakmal leaves it alone.
Looped up ball on the off stump, Lakmal defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter on off, Dickwella reverse sweeps it to third man for a single.
Floated outside off, Lakmal leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off, Lakmal nudges it towards cover with soft hands and gets a single.
Tossed up on off, Dickwella plays a classic front foot defense.
Slowly loops it up on middle, Dickwella milks it to long on for a single.
Floated on off, SL defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Dickwella comes down the track and strokes it to long on for one.
Flights one on off, Lakmal keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Lakmal defends it off the front foot.
Suranga has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

In the air but safe! Tossed up on off, Lakmal throws his bat at it. He gets a top edge on it. It flies right over the bowler's head. Raval runs in from mid on and Santner comes running in from mid off. Santner shouts mine, he puts a good dive but the ball falls agonisingly wide of Santner. Brilliant effort from the left-arm spinner.
Tossed up outside off, Lakmal leaves it alone.
Tossed up outside off, Dickwella leaves it alone.
On the pads, Niroshan flicks it to mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Dickwella blocks it towards cover.
Tossed up on middle, Dickwella strokes it towards mid on for one.
On the stumps, Lakmal defends it off the front foot.
Lakmal sees the day off. Looped up delivery on off, Suranga keeps it out to get through the day with no more further damage. STUMPS ON DAY 2.

A chance of a run but Dickwella does not take it. This is on a length and around off, the ball shapes away a touch. Dickwella looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards deep point. Lakmal wants a run and he is halfway down the track but Dickwella sends him back.
Back of a length delivery on the off stump, Dickwella defends it off the back foot towards cover.
Beaten! Good length delivery outside off stump, Dickwella attempts to fend at it but misses it completely.
Loses his line this time does Boult. This one is bowled down the leg side and Niroshan attempts to flick but does not get any bat on it.
Good length ball on the middle pole, ND plays it back to the bowler.
A good nut to end! A maiden to begin with by Boult. This is on a length again and around off, shapes away once again. Dickwella looks to defend but it goes off the outer half to gully.
Loopy delivery on the middle, Lakmal blocks it out.
Shorter in length this time, Lakmal rocks back and cuts it straight to the cover fielder.
Beautiful delivery! Flighted delivery on off stump and it spins away from Suranga. The batsman tries to defend but gets beaten due to the spin.

FOUR! First boundary of the day for the hosts. Shorter in length this time outside the off pole. Lakmal rocks back and slaps it hard and this time it goes past the cover fielder for a boundary. The trail is now below 20.
A single now as that fielder has been pushed back! Floats it up on off, Lakmal pushes it through covers for one.
Loopy delivery on middle stump, Dickwella goes for his trademark sweep and the ball goes towards fine leg. Lakmal will be on strike for the next over.
On a good length on middle, Lakmal flicks it to square leg.
Good length delivery outside off, Lakmal shoulders his arms to this one.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Lakmal looks to cut but misses it due to the seam movement on this one.
Good length delivery on the off pole, Lakmal attempts to drive but gets a thick outside edge towards mid on.

SIX! Top edge but it goes all the way! That was with the wind and hence, it carried over. This stand continues to Frustrate New Zealand. Boult goes short and on middle, Lakmal looks to pull it but the ball hits the top edge and clears the fine leg fence.

Boult bowls it down the leg side, Lakmal looks to flick but misses it. It goes towards the keeper who fails to collect the ball and it goes past him. The batsmen take a run. The umprie gives it as a bye.
Another very good shot by Lakmal! This is shorter and outside off, Lakmal slaps it through covers for one. The deficit is below 10 now.
Dickwella works this one with the turn through square leg for one.
On the middle pole, Lakmal defends it out.
Flatter and on off, it comes off slow of the surface and also turns away. Lakmal looks to defend but the ball hits the higher part of the bat but lands safe on the off side.
BEATEN! This lands on off and then turns away. Lakmal plays the original trajectory but is beaten.
Beaten again! Patel gives it a lot of air this time and lands it outside off, Lakmal goes hard after it but the ball spins away and beats the outside edge.
Short delivery outside the off stump, Dickwella guides it to third man for a single
OUCH! Banged in by Boult, aimed at the body. Lakmal attempts to flick it but misses and gets hit flush on the elbow. Suranga is in pain while the ball goes towards point.
Another short delivery from Trent, Lakmal plays this comfortably towards cover.

OUT! Chops it on! Suranga Lakmal's handy, handy innings comes to an end. He has really done a fine job with the bat. He was probably shaken up after being hit on the elbow. Coming to the ball now, it is a back of a length delivery on the off stump, Lakmal goes for a wild hoick but gets an inside edge back to the off stump. An excellent partnership of 81 runs comes to an end. Sri Lanka trail by 7.
Beautiful delivery from Boult. It was a full delivery outside the off stump. Embuldeniya attempts to defend but misses due to the swing on it.
Another beauty to end! This is on off and it shapes away. Embuldeniya looks to defend but is beaten by the movement.
FOUR! Very good shot from Niroshan Dickwella. Flighted delivery on middle, Dickwella comes down the track and flicks it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Tossed up on middle, Dickwella blocks it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Dickwella looks to play the reverse sweep but misses it and gets hit on the glove.

NOT OUT! Indeed Dickwella is in. Flighted delivery on middle, Dickwella flicks it towards mid-wicket and goes for a quick single. Kane Williamson at mid-wicket throws the ball to the keeper and he whips the bails off in a flash. It is referred upstairs. The replays show that Dickwella was comfortably in. A direct hit would have got Dickwella in trouble.
Tossed up on middle, Embuldeniya looks to defend but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Flighted delivery on middle, Embuldeniya looks to defend but again gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length delivery on the middle stump, Dickwella flicks it towards mid-wicket and calls Embuldeniya for a quick double. Scores level
On a good length ball on the pads, Dickwella guides it to fine leg but refuses the single.
This is way too short outside off, Dickwella lets it be.
Good length delivery on the off pole, Dickwella pushes it towards mid-wicket and this time takes a single. 250 up for the hosts.
Good length delivery on the middle stump, Embuldeniya gets an inside edge towards fine leg. A single is not taken.

Excellent delivery from Boult. It was a short delivery on the off pole. Embuldeniya looks uncomfortable fending at it and the ball just whizzes past the bat. The bowler and the keeper think that it was out and put in a huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The Kiwis think about a review but opt against it and rightly so, as the replays show that the ball had hit the shoulder rather than the bat.
Floats it up on off, Dickwella looks to defend but it goes off the inner half on the leg side.
Another tossed up ball on middle, it is kept out.
Outside off, Dickwella pads it away.

A single now as this is worked with the turn through square leg. Fifty for him, an excellent comeback into the side. 12th in this format. He came out to bat when Sri Lanka were in trouble and now has taken them into a good position. He is still not done though.
Very full on off, the batter pushes it to mid off.
Plays the two balls out nicely! On off and it is flatter. Embuldeniya keeps it out.
Good length delivery on the pads, Dickwella flicks it towards square leg and refuses the single.
On a good length ball on the middle stump, Dickwella defends it off the back foot towards the leg side.
Shorter in length this time, Dickwella leaves it alone to the keeper.
Back of a length delivery on the off pole, Dickwella pushes it to cover and takes a single. Embuldeniya now has to face two balls to survive.

NOT OUT! It is going down leg! New Zealand lose their last review. Boult bowls this full and on the pads, Embuldeniya looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal follows but the umpire shakes his head. After a chat, Williamson signals the 'T'. Replays roll in and they show that the ball is going down leg.
Good length delivery on the off stump, Embuldeniya defends it towards the off side. Embuldeniya has managed to survive the two balls.
Floats it up on off, Dickwella keeps it out.
Nicely played! Dickwella comes down the track and also stays leg side of the delivery, he hits it wide of long off for two.
Gives it a lot of air outside off, Dickwella looks to sweep but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Gives it a lot of air outside off, Dickwella looks to sweep but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Takes the single which means Embuldeniya has one ball to play out. This is tossed up on off, Dickwella pushes it through covers for one.
A waste of a delivery! This is fired outside off, the batter lets it be.
Good length delivery on the middle pole, Dickwella pushes it towards mid off and refuses to take a single.
Back of a length delivery on the off stump, Dickwella flicks it towards the leg side and once again does not take a single.

FOUR! Good shot from Niroshan. He is going on his merry way here. It was as short delivery on the body, Dickwella rocks back and pulls it towards the fine leg fielder for a boundary. Excellent batting from Dickwella. The lead is above 10 now.
Good length delivery this time on the off pole, Dickwella pushes it to wide mid off and takes a single. Embuldeniya has to face two balls in the over.
NASTY! Short ball aimed at the body. Embuldeniya uncomfortably fends at it but gets hit flush on the gloves. Embuldeniya looks in serious pain here and has removed his gloves off.
Very full delivery aimed at the middle stump, Lasith does well to keep it out and gets through another over.

OUT! Straight to the man! The last recognized batter for Sri Lanka is making his way back. He has done a fine, fine job though. Clever bowling this by Somerville. He sees Dickwella come down the track and floats it wide outside off. Dickwella has to reach for it, he does so, hits it nicely but does not keep it down and straight to Williamson at short cover who takes a good catch. With Dickwella gone now, one would believe the lead won't be a very threatening one. For now it is 13. A wicket to go though.
Loopy delivery on the middle pole, Lahiru blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Lahiru lets it go.
Shorter in length this time, LK defends it to the off side.
Flatter delivery on the off stump, Lahiru defends it towards the cover fielder.
Loopy delivery outside the off stump, Lahiru blocks it out off the front foot towards the off side. Good over from Somerville. A wicket and no runs from it.

FOUR! Very handy runs for Sri Lanka. Boult bowls a short delivery, Embuldeniya looks to pull but it goes off the helmet towards fine leg for a boundary. The umpire feels there is bat involved and he gives it as a boundary.

On a good length and outside off, Embuldeniya looks to go big but gets a top edge. It goes towards third man where the fielder collects the ball in one bounce. The batsmen cross ends. Lasith Embuldeniya looks in pain as he got hit on the helmet in the previous ball.
Good length delivery on off, Kumara blocks it off the back foot.
Bowls a bouncer, Kumara does well to duck under it.
Bowls a yorker on off, Kumara does well to dig it out.
Bowls a yorker on middle, Kumara manages to dig it out.
Loopy delivery outside the off stump, Embuldeniya pushes it to cover.

OUT! Three reds and there is the last wicket! Somerville gets it. It was a review in hope by the batter as it always looked out. A loopy delivery on the middle stump, Lasith Embuldeniya attempts to sweep but misses the ball and gets hit on the pads. The Kiwis go in for a loud appeal and the umpire has no hesitation in giving it out. Embuldeniya goes for the review in desperation. The replays roll in and the Hawk Eye shows that it was hitting the stumps. SRI LANKA ARE BOWLED OUT FOR 267! THEY LEAD BY 18!
Starts with a good length delivery on the pads, Raval gets hit on the pads while defending it. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved.
On a good length on the leg stump, Raval defends it towards mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on the off stump, Raval defends it towards gully.
Back of a length delivery, Jeet blocks it back to the bowler.
Another back of a length delivery on the off stump, Raval pushes it back towards the bowler.
On a good length this time from Lakmal, Jeet defends it again. Good start from Suranga Lakmal as it is a maiden.
Floats it up on off, it pitches and turns away. Latham lets it be.
Slows it up and lands it on off, it pitches and once again spins away. Latham looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards point.
Flatter and quicker and on off, Latham works it to mid-wicket.
Shorter and quicker again on off, Tom defends it.
Outside off and spinning away further. Latham lets it be.
On middle, Latham goes back and defends it onto the ground. Two maidens in a row!
Good length ball on the pads, Raval flicks it towards square leg and takes a single. Raval and New Zealand are off the mark.
OHH! Good delivery from Lakmal. It was a good length delivery around the off stump. Latham leaves it alone but the ball just whizzed past the off stump. It is a good leave in the end from Latham.
On a good length on the off stump, Latham gets an inside edge attempting to push it towards the off side, onto his boots and rolls towards the off side.
Back of a length delivery outside the off stump, Latham lets it go back to the keeper.
On a good length outside the off stump, Latham has no business with it and lets it go back to the keeper.
Good length delivery on the off stump, Latham defends it off the back foot back to the bowler.
Flatter and on off, this is defended.
A couple! This is outside off and flatter, Raval plays it late and down towards third man for two.
Shorter and on off, Raval pushes it to covers.
On the stumps again but the length is shorter, Raval goes back and pushes it back to the bowler.
A little fuller this time, Raval lunges and keeps it out.
Outside off, it is left alone.
NO BALL! Lakmal oversteps here. It is a good length delivery outside the off stump. Latham lets it go back to the keeper.
On a good length on the off pole, Latham defends it back to the bowler.
Another good length delivery on the middle pole, Latham flicks it towards mid-wicket for a quick single. The fielder has a shy at the stump but Raval is well in.
BOUNCER! A good one from Lakmal. Raval does not play at it and ducks under it. The umpire does not give it a wide as he thinks it is fine.
Loses the line does Lakmal, It was a short ball on the pads and Raval lets it go back to the keeper.

Not out!  Fuller in length this time on the pads, Raval gets hit on the pads while trying to flick it. The Sri Lankans put in a huge appeal for LBW but the umpire does not give it out. They think for a review but opt against it. In the end it was a good decision as the ball was going down the leg side.
BOUNCER! Lakmal pitches this one outside off stump and the ball rises to the keeper. Raval shoulders arms to it.
Flighted delivery on off, Latham defends it off the back foot.
Tossed up outside off, Latham lets it go.
Floated delivery on off, Latham punches it to point.
Outside off, Latham leaves it alone.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham keeps it out.
Tossed up outside off, Latham does not bother to play at that.
Lakmal bowls a short delivery, Raval pulls it through square leg for a run.
On a good length and outside off, Latham shoulders his arms to this one.
BEATEN! On a good length and outside off, Latham looks to defend but misses it due to the away movement on this one. Dickwella appeals for a caught behind but the umpire shakes his head.
Good length delivery on off, Latham blocks it off the back foot.
On a good length on off, Latham drives it straight back towards the bowler.
Length delivery on middle, Latham flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Loopy delivery on the middle pole, Latham defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery outside the off stump, Latham prods forward and pushes it towards mid on for a single.
Another flighted delivery on the middle pole, Raval defends it back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! New Zealand lose their first wicket even before they cut their deficit. Dhananjaya de Silva is the man who draws first blood for Sri Lanka. A soft dismissal this. De Silva bowls this on off, the ball comes slow off the surface. Raval looks to push at it but is already into the shot. The ball ends up chipping it to the fielder at cover where Karunaratne makes no mistake. Early wicket for Sri Lanka, just what they would have wanted. They would be eager for another before the Lunch interval.

OVERTHROWS! Loopy delivery on the off stump, Williamson defends it to the off side and takes a single. The fielder throws it at the stumps but misses. It is a wayward throw and the ball goes past the keeper allowing the batsman to take another run. Unnecessary from Sri Lanka this.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Williamson pushes it towards cover.
This is on the pads, Latham works it down to fine leg for one.
Good length delivery on the off stump, Kane plays it late towards the gully fielder.
NO BALL! Lakmal oversteps once again. It was a back of a length delivery on the middle stump, Williamson defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length this time on the middle pole, Kane plays it back to the bowler.
Full in length on the off stump, Williamson guides it to the mid on fielder. No run.
On a good length on the off stump, Kane guides it towards third man and takes a single.
Good length ball on the middle pole, Latham flicks it to fine leg and crosses over for a single.
Floats it up outside off, it has been left alone.
Shorter in length outside the off stump, Latham cuts it past cover for a single.
Loopy delivery on the middle stump, Kane defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter in length this time on the middle stump, Williamson plays it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on the middle pole, Kane plays it towards short leg.
Short delivery on the middle stump, Williamson flicks it to the leg side. No run.
Flatter and on off, Latham goes back and keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Latham comes down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Shorter delivery outside the off stump, Latham cuts it to cover and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on the off pole, Williamson prods forward and pushes it towards cover.
Looped up ball on middle stump, Kane defends it off his front foot back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Williamson has blocked it back to the bowler.
Flatter and on middle, this is worked through square leg for a couple. Scores level now.
On off, Latham pushes it to covers.
Flighted ball on middle, this is defended.
Another loopy ball on off, blocked.
On stumps, this is defended.
This is angled into the pads, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery on the pads, Kane flicks it towards short leg.
Flighted delivery on the middle stump, Kane defends but the ball almost rolls on back to the stumps. It hits the pad of Williamson and it rolls to first slip.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Kane defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Kane guides it to third man. No Run.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Kane flicks it to mid on.

Just, just! That missed the off pole by a whisker. This is floated up on off, Williamson defends outside the line. It hits the inside edge and rolls agonizingly close past the off pole. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Flighted delivery on off, Latham defends it off the front foot.
BEATEN! Tossed up outside off, Latham looks to defend but misses it due to the spin on this one.
Floated delivery on middle, Latham flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single. New Zealand get into the lead now.
Flighted delivery on middle, Williamson comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen cross ends.
Outside off, Latham leaves it alone.
Tossed up on middle, Latham defends it out.
Full toss on off, Williamson drives it to covers.
Tossed up on middle, Williamson comes down the track and keeps it out.
Floated delivery on off, the skipper drives it to mid off.

OUT! In the air... Kusal Perera seems to have misjudged it but he hangs on in the end. Falls on his back. A huge, huge wicket for Sri Lanka. They have got New Zealand's best batter with the lead at 2. Body blow this for New Zealand as they needed a big effort from their skipper but it is not to be. Williamson was getting bogged down and he looks to break free here. He steps down the track to this flighted delivery on middle. He does not get to the pitch of the ball but still goes ahead with the shot. He only manages to hit it high in the air behind mid on. Perera runs back, he does not seem very comfortable under it but still manages to take it behind him. The Lankans are ecstatic and Williamson walks back disappointed. Back-to-back failures for him. You do not see that often. Sri Lanka right on top here.
Latham works it with the angle towards mid-wicket for one.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket. They pick up a single.
Akila floats one down the leg side, Taylor looks to flick but luckily he does not get any feather on it.
Dananjaya gives this one a lot of air and bowls it on middle, Taylor milks it to long on and eases to the other end.
Tossed up on off, Latham calmly defends it off his front foot.
Akila goes short around off, Latham gets on his back foot and punches it to cover.
Arm ball outside off, Latham reads it well and leaves it alone.
Flighted on off and middle, Latham bends his back and defends it to get through the over.
Loopy delivery on the middle stump, Taylor comes down the track and plays it to mid on for a single.
Flatter delivery on the leg stump, Latham rocks back and flicks it to square leg for a single.

OUT! Caught! It is getting bad to worse here for New Zealand. Don't know what Taylor was thinking here. His side are already two down and yet he goes for a counter-attacking approach which is not needed at all at this stage. Embuldeniya bowls a flighted ball outside off, Taylor comes down the track and goes for a big smash on the off side. The ball spins away and takes the outside edge of the bat. It goes straight to Dhananjaya de Silva at first slip, who is one of the best Sri Lankan fielders. He won't drop those and he does not. Second wicket for Lasith Embuldeniya and it's two massive fishes here.
Flighted on leg, Nicholls guides it to short fine leg.
Another flighted delivery, Nicholls flicks to square leg and gets off the mark with a single..
Shorter in length this time, Latham tries to flick it on the leg but it falls just short of the short fine leg fielder. Excellent over from Embuldeniya.
Slower and shorter on middle and leg, Nicholls defends it.
Tossed up on middle, Henry keeps it out.
Flighted delivery on the middle pole, Nicholls defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on the middle stump, Nicholls defends it to the off side.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Nicholls blocks it out.
Bowls a flighted delivery on the off stump, Nicholls attempts to defend it but gets an outside edge towards the slip region.

NOT OUT! Latham is safely home! Tossed up on middle and leg, Latham comes down the track and tucks it towards mid on and calls for a quick single. Mathews gets to the ball and scores a direct hit at the bowler's end. The ball deflects behind and they take a second run. The umpire goes to the T.V umpire and replay shows Latham is safely in.
FOUR BYES! Floated on the pads, it spins away from the batsman. Latham looks to flick but misses. Dickwella too misses to collect and the ball goes behind to the fine leg fence.

SIX! If you hit it then hit it clean and that is exactly what Latham has done here. Tossed up delivery on middle and leg, Tom comes down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and heaves it over the mid-wicket fence for a biggie. No one in the deep so once he got any sort of decent connection he was going to be safe.
On the pads, Latham turns it to leg gully.
Shorter on off, TL strokes it to point for a single.
Tossed up on the pads, Henry glances it to the on side and keeps the strike.
Loopy delivery outside the off stump, Nicholls lets it go.
FOUR! First Boundary for Nicholls. It was a short delivery on the pads and Nicholls just flicks it towards the deep mid-wicket boundary.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Nicholls defends it back to the bowler
Flighted delivery outside the off stump, Henry blocks it back to the bowler.
Looped up ball on middle, Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Henry blocks it out.
Floated on the pads, Latham glances it to the on side.
Tossed up on middle, Latham keeps it out.
FOUR! Swept and swept with authority! Flighted on middle and off, Latham gets down on one knee and sweeps it through square leg for a boundary. He is set now and holds the  key here for New Zealand.
Shorter on leg, Latham flat-bats it against the spin towards mid-wicket for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
Flighted on the pads, Nicholls flicks it to the on side and keeps the strike.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Henry blocks it towards the off side.
Shorter in length, Nicholls rocks back and pushes it to cover for a single.
Flighted delivery outside the off stump, Latham lets it go.
Flatter delivery on the middle pole, Latham flicks it to mid-wicket.
Shorter delivery on off stump, Latham rocks back and cuts it to point.

FOUR! Flighted delivery on the middle pole, Tom sweeps it nicely towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. Latham is looking really good here and has to continue the good work in order for the the Kiwis to get a substantial lead.
Shorter on the pads, Nicholls glances it towards mid-wicket for one.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Latham comes down the track and defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle, Latham sweeps it towards fine leg for a single.
Flighted on the stumps, Nicholls blocks it off the front foot.
On the pads, Nicholls flicks it without any fuss towards the leg side for a single.
Shorter on the pads, Latham turns it with the spin wide of the man at leg slip. The fielder from slip cleans it up before the ropes saving a run.
Loopy delivery outside the off stump, Latham pushes it towards cover for a single.
Flighted delivery on the off pole, Nicholls gets a thick outside edge  towards first slip where the ball falls short.
Looped up ball on off, Nicholls defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on the middle pole, Henry Nicholls flicks it away to square leg for a single.
Full delivery on the middle pole, Latham goes for the slog sweep towards the square leg region where the fielder from deep mid-wicket  runs in and makes an excellent diving stop. Two runs taken.
Shorter delivery on the off stump, Latham defends it off the back foot.
Floated on off, Nicholls defends it off the inner half of his bat.
Tossed up on middle, Nicholls strokes it to mid on.
Shorter around off, Nicholls looks to cut but gets a thick outside edge wide of first slip for one.
Floated on off, Latham sweeps it to the on side for one.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Latham comes down the track and tucks it towards mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on middle, Latham defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on the middle stump, Latham blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Nicholls gets an inside edge towards third man and takes a single. The lead is now 50 with that single.
BEATEN! Loopy delivery on the middle. Nicholls misses the ball completely due to the turn on it.
Shorter delivery outside the off stump, Nicholls rocks back and cuts it towards the cover region for a single.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Latham drags it to fine leg and gets a single to take the partnership to 45.
Slower through the air on off and middle, Latham comes down the track and nudges it to long on for a single.
Flatter on off and middle, Nicholls comes down the track and blocks it.
Nicholls is not letting the ball turn here as he once again charges down and blocks it on the full.
Loopy ball on the stumps, Henry stays in his crease this time and defends it.
Tossed up on the pads, Henry charges and glances it to mid-wicket for a run.
Short and straight outside off, Latham defends it off the upper half of his bat. The ball pitches on the crease and hits the pads of Dickwella.

NOT OUT! Flighted delivery on the off stump, Nicholls goes for the slog sweep but gets hit on the thigh pad. There is a big appeal for LBW but they are turned down. The hosts think of a review but opt against it. In the process, the ball goes towards the third man region and the batsman take a couple.
Shorter delivery outside the off stump, Nicholls rocks back and pushes it towards the cover region for a single.

FOUR! Too short and it is the leg spinner on off, Latham picks it, he goes back and pulls it past mid on for a boundary. Up comes the 50-run stand, very vital one. They need to keep going though. The lead is only 61 at the moment.
Another appeal but not given! This is outside off, Latham looks to paddle sweep but misses. It hits the pads and goes towards third man for two.

OUT! EDGED AND GONE! Akila Dananjaya gets the breakthrough. A much-needed one as this partnership was going along really nicely. Latham walks back after getting a start and Sri Lanka continue to control the game. Akila pitches this on middle, it turns away square. Latham defends inside the line. The ball goes off the outside edge towards second slip. Thirimanne there takes a good low catch. New Zealand are effectively 63 for 4.
On off, this is guided to point. End of a successful over by Akila.
On the pads, Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
Floated on the pads, Henry glances it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Watling is off the mark with a good looking drive. Tossed up on off, BJ drives it towards cover for one.
Tossed up on off, Nicholls milks it to long off for another single.
On the stumps, Watling defends it off the front foot.
Floated outside off, Watling leaves it alone.
Looped up ball on off, Nicholls blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on the middle stump, Nicholls gets an inside edge towards square leg and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on the middle pole, Watling defends it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on middle, Watling blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on the middle stump, BJ defends it back to the bowler.
Bowls a flighted delivery on middle, Watling pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on off, Nicholls plays a sweep through square leg for a single.

NOT OUT! Excellent review and there was bat involved. Quicker and spinning away from the batsman. Watling looks to play it across the line but misses. There is a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. BJ takes the review straightaway, the man at short leg too indicates there is bat involved. Replays roll in and the Ultra Edge confirms that the ball kissed the leading edge of his bat.
Tossed up on the stumps, BJ blocks it.
On the stumps, Watling sweeps it to leg gully.
Tossed up on the stumps, Watling defends it off the front foot.
Drifted outside off, Watling shoulders arms to it to get through the over unscathed.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Loopy delivery on the middle stump, Nicholls defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on off, Nicholls defends it towards the off side.
FOUR! Excellent shot from Nicholls. It was a loopy delivery and on the middle stump, Nicholls flicks it past the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Nicholls blocks it out.
On off, this is blocked.
Floated on off, Watling defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, BJ keeps it out.
Quicker on off, BJ strokes it to the left of the bowler. Embuldeniya cannot stop it cleanly allowing the batter to take a single.
Floated on middle, HN nudges it to long on and gets to the other end.
On the pads, Watling turns it to mid-wicket.
Floated on off, BJ blocks it.
Flighted delivery outside the off stump, Nicholls lets it go.
Loopy delivery on middle, Nicholls blocks it back to the bowler.
Flatter delivery on the middle, Nicholls flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Shorter delivery, spinning into the batsman. Watling cuts towards the cover region and crosses over for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Nicholls defends it off the front foot.
Looped up ball on off, Nicholls defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.
Floated on off, Watling defends it off the front foot.
Full toss on middle, Watling turns it towards fine leg and gets a couple.
Floated on off, BJ defends it off the front foot.
On the stumps, Watling bends his back and taps the ball down onto the ground.
Floated on off, Watling lunges forward and defends it.
Very full on the stumps, Watling does well to get down.
Looped up ball on middle, Nicholls blocks it out.
Flatter delivery on the middle stump, Henry pushes it towards mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Nicholls defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery on middle, Nicholls blocks it out.
OHH! Flighted delivery on off stump, HN looks to drive but gets an outside edge towards point.
Loopy delivery on off stump, Nicholls defends it towards the bowler.
Tossed up on off, BJ keeps it out.
Floated on off, Watling blocks it.
On middle, Watling turns it towards square leg.
Loopy delivery on middle, BJ defends it classically.
On the stumps, Watling keeps it out.
Comes down the track and taps it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Nicholls plays it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery outside the off stump, Nicholls lets it go.
Flighted delivery on middle, Henry blocks it out towards the leg side.
Looped up ball on off, HN defends it to the off side.

DROPPED! Dickwella is the culprit over here. Nicholls who was well-set, gets a lucky reprieve here. It was a loopy delivery on the off stump, Nicholls who was about to leave the ball at first decides to put bat on it but can only get an outside edge to the keeper. Dickwella was not expecting it and makes a mess of the catch.
Flighted delivery outside the off pole, Nicholls lets it go.
Floated on off, Watling blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Watling drags his sweep towards backward square leg for one. Finally a run after 20 balls.
Floated around off, Nicholls now drags his sweep to square leg and rotates the strike.
Flighted on off, BJ gets on his front foot and defends it.
Drifter outside off, Watling leaves it alone.
On the stumps, Watling blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Nicholls gets on his front foot and blocks it.

OUT! Caught! Dickwella will be a relieved man as he had dropped Nicholls not too long ago. Dhananjaya was unlucky on that occassion but Kusal Mendis has not made the same error. De Silva bowls this slower through the air on off, it grips away off the surface. Nicholls looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and it goes to the left of first slip. Mendis there shows good reflexes and takes a sharp catch. Big wicket in the context of the game for Sri Lanka as Nicholls was looking very good out in the middle. Once again the Kiwis have their backs to the wall in this game. A well-deserved wicket for Dhananjaya de Silva.
Floated on off, Santner starts his innings off the front foot.
Shorter on off, Santner punches it towards cover and gets off the mark with a single.
Flighted on off, BJ keeps it out.
On the stumps, Watling defends it off the front foot to get through the over. Good over from Dhananjaya de Silva.
Loopy delivery on the off pole, Santner tries to drive it towards the off side but gets an inside edge and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on off stump, Watling defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Creamed away! Excellent shot from Watling. It was a loopy delivery outside  off, Watling dances down the track and drives it towards the mid off region. The fielder at mid off dives to make a stop but lets it go to the boundary. First boundary for Watling.
Floated on off, Watling strokes it to cover.
Flighted delivery on off stump, Watling plays it back to the bowler.
Looped up ball on off stump, BJ defends it off his front foot towards the off side.

Ohh! Play and just misses. Flighted outside off, Santner looks to drive it on the up but the ball turns away and just misses the outside edge of his bat. Luckily Santner had his feet inside the crease as Dickwella was quick to whip the bails off.
Tossed up on the stumps, Santner defends it off the front foot.
Shorter on off, Santner defends it to cover.
Floated on off, Mitchell strokes it towards cover for a single.
On the pads, Watling flicks it wide of leg gully for a run.
On the stumps, Santner keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on off stump, Watling defends it towards cover.
Flighted delivery on off, Watling defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on the off pole, Watling gets out his sweep and plays it towards fine leg for a single.
Loopy delivery on off stump, Santner while trying to defend gets an inside edge towards short leg.
Looped up ball on off, Santner defends it into ground.
Shorter delivery outside the off stump, Santner rocks back and slaps it through the cover region for a brace.
Floated on the pads, Watling turns it to square leg.

FOUR! Bad ball and rightfully punished. Dhananjaya is guilty of bowling too short on this occassion, it is on the pads too. BJ picks it early, gets on his back foot and swivels it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Follows it up with a calm front foot defense.
Floated on off, Watling keeps it out.
Tossed up on the stumps, Watling comes down the track and strokes it to long on for a run.
Short on off, Santner punches it towards cover for one.
Loopy delivery on middle, Santner plays it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Santner blocks it out.
Looped up ball on the off stump, Santner defends it towards the off side.
Flatter delivery spinning into Santner, Mitchell plays it towards long off for a single.
Loopy delivery which is taken on the full by Watling and he plays it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Santner pushes it off the back foot, back towards mid off and takes a single. The lead has moved to 100 with this single.
Tossed up on middle, Santner defends it nicely off the meat.
Floated on off, MS defends it off his front foot.
Slightly shorter on off, Santner defends it off the back foot.
Shorter on off, Santner punches it to cover.
On the stumps, Santner gets down and blocks.
Flights one on off, Santner milks it to long off for a single.
Shorter on off, Santner punches it towards cover for one.
On the pads, Watling tucks it to the on side.
Once again turns it to square leg.
On middle and leg, Watling flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Defended off the back foot by Santner.

EDGED AND DROPPED! Tough chance but still a chance. Slightly short on off, it is not short enough to cut. Santner still goes for the cut but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes quickly to the left of first slip. Mendis there gets wrong footed and misses, fails to gather it as the ball hits him on his body.
Shorter on off, Watling punches it to cover.
On the stumps, Watling blocks it off the front foot.
Short on off, Watling punches it to cover.
Tossed up on off, Watling comes down the track and milks it to long on for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Almost a disastrous run out. Shorter on off, Santner punches it wide of cover and takes a single. He wants the second but Nicholls says no and rightfully so as the fielder quickly gets to the ball.
Beauty! Flighted delivery outside off, it grips away off the surface. Santner looks to drive but misses.
On middle, this is kept out.
On middle, this is defended.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball. One run added to the total.
On the stumps again, Watling lunges and keeps it out.
Another one on the stumps, Watling prods forward and blocks it.
Loopy delivery on off, Santner defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Mitchell defends it off the front foot towards the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Santner throws his wicket away at the stroke of Tea. Yes, it was a bad ball but he could have resisted playing that shot. It is a short ball, a nothing ball down the leg side from Embuldeniya which comes slow off the surface. Santner wanted to play the pull shot but is early into it as it sticks in the surface. A top edge is induced and it goes towards the deep mid-wicket fielder. Lakmal runs forward and across and takes a simple catch. Another batter walks back after getting off to a start. Another budding stand comes to an end. Santner walks back disappointed, all the other players follow him as it is TEA ON DAY 3!
Loopy delivery on the off pole, Southee defends it to the off side.
Flighted delivery on middle, Southee defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter in length on off, Southee cuts it towards point for a single. Southee gets off the mark with that single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Southee flicks it to mid-wicket.
Very full and on off, Southee pushes it to mid off for one.
Flighted delivery on the off pole, Watling defends it to the off side.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Watling defends it to the off side.
Shorter delivery on the off stump which spun into the batsman a bit, Watling rocks back and cuts it towards point for a single.
Loopy delivery on the middle pole, Southee defends it off the front foot.
Flatter and on off, Watling goes back and pushes it through covers for one.
Flatter delivery on the middle stump, Southee defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Southee pushes it back to the bowler.
Looped up ball on middle, Southee blocks it out.
Flatter delivery on the off stump, Southee defends it towards the off side.
Loopy delivery on the middle pole, Southee pushes it to mid on for a single.
On off, blocked.
Flatter and on the pads, Southee works it to short leg.
Short ball outside off stump, Southee cuts off the back foot towards cover but the fielder makes an excellent diving stop.
Short ball on off, Southee pushes it to mid on for a single.
SAFE! Loopy ball on middle, Watling gets an outside edge which was up in the air for a while towards cover.
Flighted delivery on middle, Watling pushes it to mid off for a single.
On middle, this is worked to mid-wicket.
The batsman works it down the leg side. They pick up a single.
Shorter and on middle, Southee pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! Poor ball and put away! Short and on middle, easy pickings. Southee goes back and pulls it through square leg for a boundary.
On the pads, Southee looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
On the pads again, it is worked to mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery on the middle stump, Watling, in an attempt, to defend it edges it to first slip but it falls short of the fielder.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Watling defends to silly point.
Flighted delivery on the middle stump, Watling dances down the track and plays it back to the bowler.
Short delivery on the off stump, Watling pushes it to cover for a single.
Loopy delivery on the middle, Southee blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Southee defends it back to the bowler.
This is on middle, it is worked through square leg for one.
Flatter and outside off, this one turns back in. Southee pushes it through covers for one.
Shorter and outside off, Watling cuts it through point for one.
Loopy delivery on middle, Southee pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Southee pushes it to third man for a single.
Looped up ball on off, Watling comes down the track and plays it towards mid on and takes a quick single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Watling blocks it out.
Shorter ball on off, Watling cuts towards point and takes a single.

DROPPED! Kusal Mendis is the culprit. It was a loopy delivery on off, Southee slashes at it but gets an outside edge. The ball goes towards the gully fielder who was standing quite close. He fails to react in time and does not hang on. It was a tough chance but should have been taken at this level.
No run.  Loopy delivery on the off stump, Southee blocks it out.
Loopy ball on off, Southee pushes it to covers.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
On off, Watling defends it.
This is bowled outside off and it is turning back in. Watling looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pads.
The batsman has driven it through mid off. They pick up a single.
On off, Southee defends it back to the bowler.
On off again, Southee lunges and keeps it out.

A huge shout by the bowler but the impact is outside off. Dananjaya floats it up outside off, Southee gets his front pad outside the line of off and tries to defend. The ball turns back in and hits the pad. Akila appeals but the umpire shakes his head. Sri Lanka think about the review but then do not take it. Good they did not as it never looked out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Watling keeps it out.
Short on off, Watling makes room and slaps it through covers. The batsmen take a single.
Tossed up on leg, Southee looks to defend off the back foot but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Floated delivery on middle, Southee defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Southee flicks it towards mid-wicket. The batsmen take a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Watling comes forward and drives it through covers for a run.
Fuller delivery on the off stump, Watling flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on off which spun into the batsman. Watling flicks it towards short leg.
Looped up delivery outside off stump, Watling moves towards the off side and flicks it to short leg.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Watling blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Watling defends it back to the bowler.
Looped up ball on off, Watling blocks it out.
Good length and on off, Southee defends it out.
BEATEN! In the corridor of uncertainty. Southee pokes at it and gets beaten.
Good length ball on off, Southee pushes it towards cover and takes a single.
Good length ball on off, Watling rocks back and pushes it towards cover for a single.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Southee flicks it to mid-wicket. No run.
Good length delivery on the off pole, Southee pushes it to point.
Loopy delivery on middle, Watling flicks it to short leg.
Flighted delivery on middle, Watling pushes it to short leg.
Fuller delivery which is converted to a low full toss by Watling as he dances down the track and pushes it to mid off.
Loopy delivery on middle, Watling defends it to short leg.
Short ball on off stump, Watling rocks back and slaps it towards the cover region and takes a brace.

NOT OUT! There is bat involved. It was a loopy delivery on middle stump, Watling looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. There is a big appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. The Sri Lankan players, after a chat, opt for the review. The replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows that it is off the inside edge. Sri Lanka have lost one of their reviews.
On a good length and outside off, Southee plays it to covers.
Good length delivery on off, Southee defends it off the back foot.
On a length on middle, Southee flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen pick up a couple.
Lakmal bowls a short of a length delivery, Southee pulls it over mid-wicket. Dhananjaya de Silva in the deep does well to stop it with a dive and saves two runs for the team.
On a length on middle, Southee flicks it towards square leg for a run.
Short of a length delivery, Watling pulls it towards fine leg for a run.
Loopy delivery on the middle stump, Watling plays it back to the bowler.
Shorter in length on off, Watling pushes it to cover.
Short ball on off stump, which spun into the batsman, Watling rocks back and flicks it towards fine leg for a single.
Loopy delivery on the middle stump, Southee tries to pull but the ball goes in between the legs as Southee misreads the spin.

Flighted delivery on the middle pole, Southee prods forward to defend but the ball gets hit on the pad and goes to short leg. There is a stifled appeal for a catch at short leg but the umpire is unmoved.
Loopy delivery on middle, Southee blocks it out.
Slightly fuller around off, Watling plays it late and down towards third man for two.

EDGY FOUR! New Zealand won't mind how they come as long as they come. This is on a length and around off, Watling looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge. He does so with soft hands though so it goes all along the ground, past the first slip fielder and into the third man fence.
Peach! Unplayable! This lands on off and then straightens. The batter defends inside the line and gets beaten.
On off again and lands it on a length. Watling keeps it out.
Back of a length around off, Watling pushes it through covers and takes one.
Direct hit but Southee is in! Good length and on middle, Southee pushes it towards mid on for a quick run.
Loopy delivery outside the off pole, Southee defends it to the off side and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Watling bends and plays it short leg.
Shorter in length which spun away from the batsman, Watling defends it to the off side.
Loopy delivery on middle, Watling pushes it to mid off and takes a single. The lead is now 150.
Flighted delivery on off, Southee blocks it out.
Looped up ball on off, Southee defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length on off, Watling defends it.
Fuller and on off, Watling once again keeps it out.
A little too straight this time, Watling works it through mid-wicket and bags a brace.
Very full this time and on middle, this is hit back to the bowler.
Shortens his length and lands it on off, defended.
Another one on a length and outside off, Watling plays it late towards point.
Loopy delivery on middle, Southee punches it to long on for a single.
Flighted delivery on the middle stump, BJ blocks it out.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot. The batsmen have run through for a single.
It was a flighted delivery on the middle pole, Southee flicks it towards leg side for a single. It hit the short leg fielder on the way towards mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Watling flicks it to square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on the middle stump, Southee defends it off the front foot.

Fifty for Watling, 17th in Tests. He generally performs during tough times and he has done exactly that here. Almost single-handedly taken New Zealand to safer shores. Needs to go on though. He gets there by cutting this short ball outside off to deep point for one.
Back of a length on off, Southee pushes it to covers for one.
Another single as Watling guides it to deep point.
BOUNCER! A good one from Lahiru. It was bowled at a perfect bouncer length and Southee tries to hook it but misses the ball completely.

DROPPED! That went right in between first slip and the keeper, both went for it, it hits the glove of the keeper and then deflects onto the first slip fielder and goes towards fine leg for one. Dickwella's positioning could be blamed. Kumara goes wide of the crease and angles it short and into the batter. Dickwella now moves leg side with the delivery. Southee looks to cut but the ball is too close to play that shot. It goes off the outside edge to the right of Dickwella. He is wrong footed but still manages to get a dive in. The ball hits the right outstretched glove but does not stick in. Deflects onto the body of Mathews who dives to his left and goes down to fine leg for one. A tough chance but had Dickwella not moved to his left, it would have been taken. They needed to break this stand. This could prove costly.
A bumper on middle, Watling ducks under it.
Tossed up on middle, Southee defends it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Southee plays a sweep towards the keeper where he fumbles.
Floated delivery on off, Southee defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on middle, Southee defends it out.

OUT! STUMPED! The dropped catch does not cost Sri Lanka a lot. Finally they manage to get the breakthrough. A very, very good partnership for the Kiwis though. Southee walks back after playing a handy innings. New Zealand are effectively 160 for 7 now. Embuldeniya gets his fourth. He tosses it up above the eye line. Seeing that, Southee comes down the track. He though is beaten by the dip and the turn away as he looks to drive. The keeper collects and whips the bails off. Sri Lanka would now really hope to take the last three wickets quickly.
A dot to end a successful over for Embuldeniya. On off, Somerville keeps it out.

NOT OUT! A big LBW shout. It is a back of a length delivery on middle, Watling tries to flick but gets hit flush on the pads. There is a strong appeal for LBW but is turned down. The Sri Lankan players think of a review but opt against it.
Another back of a length delivery outside off stump, Watling cuts it towards cover for a single.
BOUNCER! Not a good one at that. It was bowled way outside off and Somerville does not feel the need to play at it. He lets it go back to the keeper.
Good length delivery on off, Somerville pushes it to cover for a single.
FOUR! Brilliant shot from Watling. It is a full delivery on middle, Watling drives it straight past the mid on fielder for a boundary. Watling is playing an amazing knock here.

FOUR! Back to back boundaries for Watling. This one is bowled short and outside off stump. Watling just rocks back and guides it over gully for a boundary. Excellent batting this from BJ. He moves on to 60 with that shot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Somerville defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Somerville blocks it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on middle, Somerville flicks it towards mid-wicket for a run.
Flighted delivery on off, Watling blocks it off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Watling defends it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on off, Watling plays it to covers.
Good length ball around off, Somerville stands tall and punches it through cover for a couple.
Back of a length delivery on off, Somerville defends it off the back foot.
Another back of a length delivery, William blocks it out of the back foot.
Good length delivery outside off, Somerville leaves it alone.
BOUNCER! A good one at that. It was aimed at the body. Somerville does well to duck under it.
Good length ball on the off stump, Somerville defends it off the front foot. Good over from Lahiru.
Flighted delivery on middle, Watling blocks it out.
Another flighted delivery on middle, Watling comes down the track and pushes it to mid on.
Loopy delivery on middle, Watling defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery on off stump, Watling cuts towards cover and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Somerville defends it back to the bowler.
Looped up delivery on the middle stump, William blocks it out.
Lovely fielding! This is fuller and around off, Watling creams it towards cover where the fielder dives to his left and stops it. Saves at least two.
A short one but it is down the leg side. Somerville evades it.
Another short one on the body, Somerville ducks under it.
Short ball on the pads, Somerville looks to flick but gets an inside edge to the thigh pad and the ball rolls on towards fine leg.
A bumper, WS ducks under it.
On off, this is pushed to covers.
On off, Watling defends it.
Loopy ball on off, Watling lunges and keeps it out.
Floats it up on the middle stump, Watling comes down the track and works it to mid-wicket.
Floats it up outside off, Watling strokes it through covers for one.
From over the wicket, he lands it outside leg, Somerville lunges and keeps it out.
On the pads again, this is worked through square leg for one.
Turn straightaway! Flighted and full on off, William is on the front foot to play that out but it turns in to take the inside edge. It rolls wide of short leg.
Flatter through the air, around off, Somerville goes back inside the crease and defends.
Uses the spin this time. Somerville works it past short leg and gets off strike. First run of the day for the Kiwis!
Tossed up ball on middle, Watling flicks it past the left side of the leg slip fielder for a single.
Turning back in from around off, Somerville defends it comfortably in front of short leg.
Nicely defended. Slow spin back into the batsman from outside off, William sticks back and blocks it with soft hands.
Floated delivery, full and on middle, Watling lunges and defends it to the off side.
Arm ball this time, around off and skidding back in, BJ is on the back foot in defense.
Fires one in on middle, Watling covers the line, there isn't much spin and hence he defends it easily to the leg side.
Embuldeniya gives this one a good toss. Lands it full and on off, Watling leans forward in defense.
Watling has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flatter one, full and on middle, Watling defends it off the front foot to the on side. Maiden!
Starts with a nice and full delivery on off, Somerville solidly defends it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery on middle, Somerville defends it towards the off side.
Fuller in length on middle, William flicks it towards mid-wicket.
This time, Suranga bowls a short delivery outside the off stump, Somerville lets it go.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside the off stump, Somerville goes for a drive but misses it completely.

BOUNCER! A good one at that. It is aimed at the body and Somerville does well to duck under it. With a leg gully in place, the idea was to hurry up the batsman but William did well to hold his composure.
Loopy delivery on the pads, BJ defends it to the off side.
FOUR! Good shot from Watling. It was a full delivery from Embuldeniya and BJ sweeps it fine towards the fine leg region for a boundary. 200 up with that shot.
Shorter in length this time, Watling rocks back and slaps it to cover for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Somerville defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Somerville sweeps it behind square leg for a run.
Looped up ball on middle, BJ defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, William defends it towards mid on.
Good length delivery outside off stump, Somerville pokes at it but misses.
On a good length outside the off stump, Somerville leaves it alone.
Good length ball on the pads, William flicks it behind square leg and takes a single.

Back of a length delivery outside the off stump, Watling plays a cracking cut shot towards the cover-point region and takes a brace. The fielder (Thirimanne) runs in from third man and makes an excellent diving stop.
On a good length shaping away from the batsman, Watling lets it go to the keeper.
Flighted delivery around off, good drift and it spins away a bit, Somerville covers the line and makes a brave leave.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery from Embuldeniya on the off stump, William looks to defend but misses due to the away spin. That was a peach and would have put even the best batsman in a spot.
Shorter delivery on the off stump, Somerville attempts to cut but is unable to put bat on it.
Flatter delivery on middle, William flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes a single as the bowler himself runs to the ball.
Loopy delivery on off, Watling pushes it to covers and takes a single.
Flighted delivery around the off stump, William lunges forward and drives it wide of cover and towards mid off for another run. Sensible.
Play and a miss! Back of a length delivery outside off, Somerville spots the chance to exercise his arms and throws his bat at it. Fails to make any connection though.
Good length delivery outside the off stump, swinging away from the batsman, Somerville leaves it alone.
Another outswinger outside off stump, William leaves it alone.
Lakmal keeps bowling it outside the off pole, Somerville has no problems in leaving it alone.
Good length delivery outside the off stump, Somerville shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on the off pole, William defends it towards the point region and takes the single.
Flighted delivery on off, William pushes it to cover.
Looped up ball on middle, Somerville flicks it to short leg.
Flighted delivery on middle, Somerville blocks it out.
Shorter in length on off, WS pushes it off the back foot towards point.

FOUR! Edgy but effective! It is an arm ball from Embuldeniya which is close to the off stump. William still goes for the cut and it goes off the outside edge between the first slip and the second slip fielders towards the third man fence.
Slower through the air, full and around off, Somerville is on the front foot as he gently pushes it to covers. Very solid. The lead is closing in on 200!
Good length delivery in the channel outside off, Watling has a good look at it before making a leave.
Another delivery on a length outside off, going straight on after landing, Watling covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Good length delivery on middle, Watling plays it back to the bowler.
On a good length on off, Watling defends it to the off side and takes a single.
Another good length delivery on the middle pole, William blocks it towards mid off.

Lakmal bowls a good length delivery on the off pole, Somerville brings his bat down just in time and gets it away off a thick outside edge. It moves towards the point region and they take a single. The lead moves on to 198.
Fullish and on off, it's defended back off the front foot.
Tossed up ball on off, turning in sharply, William gets his bat down in time to keep it towards square leg.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Loopy and outside off, turning  back in, Somerville strides forward to defend it back but it spins back in to beat the inside edge.
Floated delivery, full and close to off, William defends it close to his front pad.
Beaten! Off spinner landing outside off, William tries to defend but it spins past his bat. Maiden from Dananjaya, lead remains two short of 200!
Good length delivery in the zone outside off, Watling pushes it out with an angled bat towards gully.

Shout for an lbw! Not given. It is on a good length which jags back in and it hits Watling on the pads. There is a loud appeal for LBW but it's turned down. The Sri Lankans think of a review but opt against it. The replays show that the ball was just clipping the leg stump. It would have been umpire's call had they taken the review.
On a good length delivery on middle, Watling pushes it off the back foot towards the leg side.
Fractionally short and close to off, Watling plays late and eases it past the diving gully fielder for a run. 199 is the lead!

Stifled appeal for an lbw! Again not entertained by the umpire. Easily going down. An inswinger by Lakmal, landing on a length around middle, Somerville fails to flick and is pinged on the pads. Lakmal appeals but soon realized his fate.
Angles in a length ball close to off, Somerville defends it from the back foot.
Shorter delivery on middle, turning into the batsman, Watling flicks it to the leg side for a single. The lead is now 200.
Flighted delivery on middle, Somerville defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter delivery which was bowled slower through the air. Somerville  pushes it easily towards the cover region and takes a single.
Quicker and fuller on middle, helped on the leg side towards mid-wicket.
Pulls his length back and bowls it short on middle, Watling gets on the back foot and taps it down to mid-wicket again.
Watling uses his feet this time to come out of the crease. He, then, drives it through covers for a couple of runs.
Back of a length delivery outside the off stump, Somerville goes for the cut off the back foot but outside edges it. Luckily for him, it falls just short of the gully fielder.
On a good length on the off pole, William pushes it to point and takes a single.
On a length and outside off, Watling lets it go to the keeper.
Loses his line here does Lakmal. It is bowled way down the leg side. Watling looks to flick but misses.
On a good length on middle, Watling plays it back to the bowler.
Fuller in length on the off pole, Watling blocks it towards the off side. Good over from Lakmal.
Flighted delivery on middle, Somerville lunges forward and defends it towards the leg side.
Looped up ball on off, William dances down the track and pushes it to mid off and goes for a quick single. The fielder has a direct hit at the bowler's end but the batsman is well in.
Flighted delivery on middle, Watling flicks it to short leg.
Looped up ball on off, Watling blocks it out.
Shorter on top of middle, Watling goes back and punches it to short mid-wicket.
Floated on off, Watling lunges forward and blocks.
Back of a length delivery on off, William pushes it to cover.
On a good length on the off stump, WS plays it towards the cover-point region and takes a single.

OUT! Caught! Lahiru strikes! He has been waiting for his chance to bowl and has delivered as soon as he got hold of the ball. Lahiru hits the deck hard around off, it is in the corridor of uncertainty. Watling looks to defend but the extra pace and a hint of away movement get the better of him as he ends up getting a thick outside edge to the keeper. Dickwella takes an easy catch. Dimuth might have missed a trick here not getting Kumara earlier on but as the saying goes - Better late than never! End of a brilliant knock from BJ. He has played a critical role with the lower order batsmen and his efforts have taken his side to the lead of 206. End of the 46-run stand but a knock to remember from Watling, deserved a hundred but will have to be satisfied now with 77.
On a good length on the off pole, Trent defends it off the back foot towards mid off.
BOUNCER! Good bowling from Lahiru. Bowled at the body. Boult uncomfortably tries to fend at it but misses it.
Full delivery on middle, Boult does well to block it out. Excellent first over by Trent!
BEATEN! Flighted delivery outside the off stump, William goes for the drive but gets beaten in air.
Looped up delivery on off, Somerville drives this towards the cover fielder and takes a single.

FOUR! First boundary for Boult. It is a full toss and Boult lunges forward and hits it straight down the ground for a boundary. Valuable runs these for the Kiwis. The lead moves to 211 with that shot.

Flighted delivery outside off, Boult comes across and looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him on his pad and there is an appeal for LBW but the umpire says no. Boult seemed to be a bit nervous as for some reason in a funny manner he points to the ball and lunges forward making it look like he was going to pick it up for a moment.
Tossed up around off, Boult gets his front foot ahead and flicks it wide of short leg towards mid on.
Off spinner on off, Boult tucks it with the spin wide of mid-wicket for a couple.
On a good length ball on off stump, William pushes it to mid off.
Back of a length delivery on the off pole, Somerville punches this off the back foot towards the cover region and take a brace. The fielder at cover runs behind it and cleans it up.
BOUNCER! This one is way outside off and Somerville ducks under it.
Fuller delivery on off, Somerville drives this nicely but doesn't get it past the cover fielder.
Back of a length delivery, WS punches it towards the off side.
On a good length on off, Somerville defends it from the crease.
Starts his new spell with a floated delivery on off, Boult gets behind the ball and blocks it.
Slightly short and spinning away, Boult leaves it alone showing he is fully aware of his off stump.
Loopy delivery on the off stump line, Boult defends it off the front foot.

FOUR! Excellent use of the feet from Boult. It was a flighted delivery on off. Boult dances down the track and plays a lofted drive over the cover fielder for his second boundary. The ball goes between the long off and cover fielders.

SAFE! Boult never left and hence the lack of confidence from the Sri Lankan players. Flighted delivery on off, there is spin and bounce on this one. Boult looks to play a cover drive to follow up the boundary but misses. Dickwella takes the bails off in a flash and puts in an appeal. Boult looks in but the square leg umpire takes no chance and takes it upstairs. One replay is enough for the T.V umpire to show NOT OUT on the giant screen.
Another play and miss. Floated around off, Boult looks to drive on the up again but once again misses.
Shorter delivery aimed at the body, Somerville blocks it out.
On a good length, on the off pole line, WS defends it towards the off side.
Another one on a length on off, Somerville pushes it towards mid off.
Good length delivery on the middle stump line, Somerville pushes it towards the cover region and gives Boult the strike.
Shorter delivery outside the off stump line, Boult goes for the cut but is unable to put any bat on it.
OHH! This time Lahiru bowls this fuller aimed at the middle stump, Boult made room for himself towards the off side but still manages to flick it towards square leg for a single.
Tossed up on middle, Boult comes down the track and negates the spin. He glances it wide of long on and gets a brace.
Full delivery on the middle stump, Boult goes for the reverse sweep but hits it straight to third man.
Fuller delivery which is converted to a full toss by Boult and played towards mid on for a single.
FOUR! Brilliant shot from Somerville. It is a flighted delivery on middle, William goes for a slog sweep and hits it towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. The lead moves to 228.
Bowls it quicker just wide of the leg stump, Somerville looks to flick but misses.
Floated around off, it is slightly short and spinning in. William waits for it and taps it towards first slip under his eyes.
Short ball on the middle stump, Boult makes room for himself and pulls it straight towards long on and takes a single.
Pacy ball down the leg side, Somerville looks to glance but misses.
Back of a length delivery on the pads, WS looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad and the ball rolls on to fine leg.
Back of a length delivery on middle, William flicks it towards mid-wicket and takes off for a single.

On a good length outside the off stump, Boult moves towards the off side and flicks it towards square leg. Boult is entertaining the fans over here. Rameez Raja on air has just called him in the Charlie Chaplin of batting! Hahaha!

Another extraordinary shot from Boult. It was a full delivery on the leg stump line, Boult makes room towards the leg side and plays a lofted drive over the bowler's head for a brace. Mathews from mid on runs back and cleans it up before it reaches the ropes.
Floated outside off, Somerville comes down the track and pads it away.
Shorter delivery spinning into the batsman, Somerville rocks back and guides it to third man and takes a single. The lead now moves to 233 with that single.

DROPPED AND SIX! Embuldeniya almost pulled out a stunner here. Tossed up on off and middle, Boult plays another brilliant shot after coming down the track. He gets to the pitch of the ball and smacks it over mid-wicket. Lasith Embuldeniya in the deep jumps and almost pulls it out of thin air but fails to hold on. The ball hits his hands and falls onto the ropes. Takes the partnership to 33 now.
Shorter delivery spinning into the batsman, Boult flicks it off his pads towards the square leg region and takes a single.
Looped up ball on off, Somerville defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on the off stump line, Somerville defends it towards the leg side.
Low full toss aimed at the middle stump, Boult who made room for himself by moving towards the leg side, drives it through the cover region and takes a brace.

OUT! Caught! Boult's cameo comes to an end! He has played an entertaining and very important knock here. Lahiru bowls it short on middle and off, Boult hangs back and plays the upper cut. He connects well but he cannot get it wide enough of third man. Dhananjaya de Silva there runs to his right and takes a simple catch. The 36-run stand has been broken. Sri Lanka will be happy to see his back as he was creating a lot of nuisance out in the middle for them. Lead is 242!
Back of a length delivery on middle, Ajaz guides it to first slip.
On a good length on middle, Ajaz pushes it to mid on.
Shorter delivery aimed at the body of Patel, the batsman rocks back and guides to cover and takes a single. Ajaz is off the mark with that single.
BOUNCER! It was a very high one from Kumara and it went way above Somerville's head. William ducks under it.
Floated on off, Ajaz strokes it towards point for one.
Flighted on off, Somerville defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, the ball spins in but does too much as Somerville looks to defend and misses to get hit on the front pad.
Floated on middle, WS nudges it to long on for one.
Flighted delivery which spun away from the batsman, Patel while trying to defend misses the ball due to the spin on it.

Shout for an LBW! It is a flighted delivery on middle turning away from the batsman, Patel goes for a defensive shot but misses and gets hit on the pads. Akila appeals but is turned down. The Sri Lankan players do not go for the review. We are done with 100 overs now, New Zealand have put themselves in a commanding position.
Shorter on the pads, William looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Floated on middle and leg, Somerville gets on his back foot and pushes it to mid on.
Tossed up on middle, Somerville milks it to long on and gets to the other end.
Flighted on off and middle, Ajaz gets down on one knee and sweeps it to square leg for a single.
Play and a miss. Flighted outside off, Ajaz looks to drive but misses.
Floated outside off, Somerville looks to sweep but misses.
Nicely looped up by Dananjaya on the off stump line, Ajaz pushes it to mid off and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Somerville flicks it towards the leg side. No run.
Flatter delivery on middle, WS flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Floated on middle and off, Ajaz defends it really well.
Tossed up outside off, Patel leaves it alone.
The lead now goes past 250. Slowly but steadily New Zealand are taking this away from Sri Lanka. Floated around off, Ajaz sweeps it towards square leg for a couple.
Loopy delivery on off, William defends it to point.
Shorter in length on off, William cuts it towards the point fielder.
Flatter delivery on middle, Somerville flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
