Flighted delivery on middle, Ajaz flicks it off the front foot towards the mid-wicket region and takes a single.
Looped up ball on middle, Somerville blocks it back to the bowler.
Short delivery on the off stump, which spun away from the batsman, Somerville looks to cut but due to the turn on it fails to put any bat on it.
Shorter on off, Ajaz gets on his back foot and defends it off the back foot.

NOT OUT! It's missing the stumps. Floated outside off, Ajaz covers his stumps and then decides to offer no shot. The ball though skids in to hit him on the pads. The Sri Lankan players appeal but the umpire says no. After a few words with his players, Dimuth signals the 'T'. Replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows that the impact is way outside off. But since Patel was not offering any shot it won't matter much. Importantly for the Kiwis, it's missing the stumps quite easily.
Floated on off, Patel defends it off the front foot.
Flights one outside off, Patel has nothing to do with it.
Floated on off, Patel strokes it towards cover for one.
Shorter on off, Somerville waits and then taps it wide of third man for a couple.
On a good length on off, Ajaz defends it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery on the off stump, Patel guides it to third man and takes a single.
Full delivery on the middle stump line, Somerville flicks it towards mid-wicket.
On a good length outside off, Somerville drives it nicely towards mid off and takes a brace. Mathews runs after it and cleans it up.
Back of a length delivery on the off stump line, Somerville guides it to third man. No run.
Good length delivery on middle, Somerville plays it towards the mid-wicket region and takes a single. The lead is now 260.
Flatter delivery on the pads, Somerville gets hit on the pads and goes towards fine leg and takes a  single.
FOUR! First boundary for Ajaz. It was a full delivery on the middle stump line. Ajaz goes for the slog sweep and hits it towards the deep mid-wicket fence for a boundary.
Floated on off, Ajaz strokes it to long off and gets to the other end.
Tossed up on the pads, Somerville glances it towards fine leg for a single.
Floated outside off, AP leaves it alone.

OUT! Just by a fraction de Silva has got the wicket. The gamble to take the review almost paid off. Flighted delivery around off, skidding back in after landing, Ajaz looks to defend but misses. The ball hits him flush on the front pad. The Sri Lankan players put in a loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Ajaz takes the review with a glimmer of hope that something goes in his favour. Replay rolls in and shows that Dhananjaya de Silva's front foot was just, just around the crease. The line belongs to the umpire and the T.V umpire is happy with his front foot's landing. He then moves onto the Ball Tracker and it shows three reds. That will be the last action before Lunch. SRI LANKA NEED 268 TO WIN!
Boult starts with a good length ball on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot. There is some swing on this one.
On a good length on off, Karunaratne keeps it out.
On a length on middle, Karunaratne flicks it through mid-wicket. The batsmen get two runs. Sri Lanka are underway.
Length delivery on middle, Karunaratne flicks it wide of mid-wicket. The batsmen get three runs.
Good length delivery on off, Thirimanne blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Thirimanne keeps it out.
Inswinging delivery first up from Southee, it is bowled on middle, Karunaratne flicks it towards square leg.
Full delivery on off stump, Karunaratne pushes it to mid off.
Another full delivery on the middle stump line, Dimuth plays it straight to mid off.
On a good length on middle, Karunaratne defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball outside off, DK is happy to let it go back to the keeper.
Fuller delivery this time from Southee, Dimuth plays it to mid on and takes off for a quick single.
Good length ball on off, it angles away just a fraction. Karunaratne defends it towards point.
Back of a length ball just outside off, Dimuth gets on his back foot and keeps it down.
Full delivery on the middle stump line, Dimuth drives it straight towards mid on.
BOUNCER! It is bowled on head height by Boult and Dimuth ducks under it
Good length delivery on middle, Karunaratne defends it towards the leg side.

Back of a length delivery outside the off stump, Dimuth drives it nicely towards the cover region and takes three. Santner goes after it and stops the ball before it reaches the fence. Karunaratne will keep strike again for the next over.
Peppering some short balls here are the Kiwis. It is on middle and leg, Karunaratne ducks under it.
Length ball on off, Dimuth gets behind it and defends it off the front foot.
Short delivery aimed at the body of the batsman, Dimuth rocks back and pulls it towards fine leg for a single.
A good inswinger from Southee. It is bowled on a good length outside off, Thirimanne lets it go to the keeper. A good leave from Lahiru.
BEAUTIFUL! Cuts Thirimanne in half. It is another inswinger from Tim and on a length, Lahiru is late to get bat on it and the ball goes between the bat and the pad.
Good length delivery outside the off stump, LT leaves it alone.
Ohh! Boult steams in and bowls a good length ball around off, Dimuth goes chasing after it but the away swinger beats Karunaratne and luckily for him he did not edge it.
Good length ball on off, Dimuth defends it off the back foot.
On a length around off, Karunaratne blocks it towards the off side.
Full delivery on middle, Karunaratne flicks it to mid on.
Back of a length delivery on the off stump, Karunaratne plays it to the cover region for a single.
On a good length outside off, Thirimanne plays it to point for a single.
Full delivery on the middle stump, Lahiru plays it to mid on.
An inswinging delivery from Southee which is bowled on off stump, Thirimanne drives it towards cover and takes a single.
Good length delivery outside off stump, Dimuth leaves it alone.
Fuller in length this time on off, Dimuth pushes it to mid on.
Good length delivery on middle, Karunaratne flicks it to square leg.
On a good length ball on off, DK defends it towards the off side.
Good length ball on off, Lahiru stands tall and punches it straight to cover.
Going down. Boult bowls a good length ball pitching on off and middle, it goes away with the angle. Thirimanne looks to defend but misses and the ball gets hit on the thigh pad.
BOUNCER! A good one at that. It is aimed at the body by Boult, Thirimanne does well to duck under it.
On a good length outside off, Thirimanne goes for the cut but misses the ball.
On a length outside off, this time Lahiru lets it go back to the keeper.
Short and spinning away, Thirimanne strokes it with the spin towards cover.
Starts with a loose full toss on middle and off, Karunaratne misses a chance to make the most of it and ends up hitting it hard close to mid on.
Much better. Short and spinning into the southpaw. Karunaratne defends it off his back foot but from the upper half of his bat.
Floated around off, Karunaratne strokes it to point and gets to the other end.
Flights one on the stumps, Thirimanne keeps it out.
Gives this one air on off and middle, Thirimanne lunges and keeps it out.
Short and spinning away, Thirimanne hangs back and punches it wide of cover to keep the strike.
Flighted around off, Thirimanne pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up on the stumps, Thirimanne defends it off the front foot.
Short on off, Thirimanne cuts it to point for a run.
Loopy delivery on the off stump line, Dimuth comes down the track and flicks it to square leg for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth defends off the front foot towards the off side.
Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne defends it towards the off side.
Looped up ball on off, Thirimanne drives it towards the cover region for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, DK gets forward and defends it towards point.

Flighted delivery on off which spun away from the batsman, Dimuth prods forward to defend but gets a thick outside edge towards first slip where the fielder dives but is unable to put any hand on it. The ball rolls to third man and they take a brace.
Looped up ball on off, Karunaratne defends it towards the off side.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth blocks it out.
A flighted delivery, landing full on middle, Thirimanne defends it back off the front foot.
Slightly short on this occasion, around off, Lahiru moves back and steers it down to third man for a run.
Uses his feet to come down the track and flicks it past the diving short leg fielder. Looks for a run but it's not there as the mid-wicket fielder runs after it.
Quicker one, full and on middle, it's worked through square leg for one.
Loopy ball on middle, Thirimanne flicks but finds short leg.
This one is pushed flatter and quicker through the air, the length is a shade short as well, Lahiru moves on the back foot in defense.
Floated ball, it lands full around off, Dimuth lunges and defends.
Beaten! Extra rev on this delivery. It drops on the rough outside off and spins away with some extra bounce. Karunaratne tries to cut but misses.
Turning away from the batsman, on the shorter side, Karunaratne cuts but finds the point fielder.
Fuller and straighter on middle, driven back to the bowler.
Lunges to a full ball and blocks it with the spin to the off side.
Somerville drags his length short and delivers it outside off, Dimuth cuts it towards the deepish cover-point fielder for a single.
Advances down the track to a full ball and drills his drive towards the bowler. Ajaz dives to his left and takes some force off it. It rolls to mid on and they cross for a run.
Flighted ball wide outside off, spinning in a bit, Thirimanne doesn't offer any shot. It seems that the ball has brushed some part of his front pad and the bowler appeals. Nothing from the umpire.
Uses the spin to his advantage and turns it off his pads to square leg for one.
Once again a flick shot played with the spin. It's in the gap at mid-wicket for a run.
The batsman works it down the leg side. One run added to the total.
Bowling a little too straight, Patel. Once again it's worked around the corner. It's to the right of the short fine leg fielder for a single.
Floated on off, Dimuth drives it but straight to short cover.

Confusion but no casualty. Short ball around off, Karunaratne cuts it wide of cover and looks for a single. Both him and Thirimanne are looking at the fielder. Latham gets to the ball quickly and Dimuth is some way down, Lahiru sends him back and luckily the skipper makes his ground.
On the stumps, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Flights one on off, Dimuth blocks it.
Shorter on off, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot this time towards cover-point.
Loopy ball on middle, Dimuth defends it off the inner half of his bat.
Starts with a flatter one on off, Thirimanne defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on the pads, Lahiru flicks it but cannot go past short fine leg.
Tossed up on off, Thirimanne defends it by getting behind the ball.
Tossed up outside off, Thirimanne pads it away. There is a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire. Lahiru had come way across and that was always going to be a difficult one to be given out.
Tossed up on off, Thirimanne blocks it off the front foot.
Maiden for Santner to begin with. Flights the last one on off, Thirimanne blocks it to get through the over.
Beauty! Somerville bowls it slower through the air on off, Karunaratne looks to defend but the ball spins away and squares him up.
Floated on off, Karunaratne pushes it to mid off.
Floats one on the stumps, Dimuth keeps it out.
Shorter on off, Karunaratne strokes it to point.
Sharp bowling. Tossed up around off, Dimuth looks to defend but once again misses it and he is again lucky to not edge that.
Shorter on off, DK punches it to cover to get through the over.
Tossed up outside off, Thirimanne gets down on one knee and reverse sweeps it towards the third man region for a single.
Floated on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Spin and bounce on this one. Tossed up outside off, Karunaratne looks to defend but misses. The ball kisses his gloves and goes on to hit him around the box.
Flighted around off, Dimuth now brings out the reverse sweep and hit it towards backward point for a single.
On the pads, Thirimanne flicks it to square leg.
On the pads and once again flicked to square leg.
Quick single. Floated on off, Karunaratne strokes it wide of mid off and gets a quick single.
Outside off, Thirimanne leaves it alone.
Once again Somerville tosses it up outside off. Asking the batsman to have a go at it but Lahiru says no and lets it carry to the keeper.
Flights one on off, Thirimanne blocks it off the front foot.
Floated outside off, Thirimanne covers his stump and leaves it alone.
On the fourth stump line, Thirimanne shoulders arms to it.
Flatter around off, Karunaratne comes down the track and tucks it wide of short fine leg.
Tossed up around off, Karunaratne looks to play the reverse sweep but it lobs off his gloves to the off side and fall in no man's land.
Floated outside off, Karunaratne comes down and pads it away.
In the air but just wide. Floated on middle and leg, Karunaratne flicks it uppishly wide of short mid-wicket. Williamson there dives like Superman to his left but cannot get his hands to the ball.

Goodness gracious, how has Thirimanne played that? Santner loops one around the eye line, Lahiru premeditates the reverse sweep but he sees the ball is full and at the very last moment, he corrects his position and blocks it.
Floated on off, Thirimanne this time defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Dimuth blocks it out towards the off side.
Loopy delivery spinning away from the batsman, Karunaratne plays it back to the bowler.
Quicker delivery aimed at the stumps, DK just manages to get his bat down in time and plays it towards short third man.
Shorter delivery on off, Dimuth rocks back and slaps it towards the cover region for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne defends it back to the bowler.
Looped up ball on off, Thirimanne leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Karunaratne turns it towards fine leg for one.
Flatter delivery on middle, Thirimanne flicks it towards square leg.
Flighted delivery on middle, Lahiru flicks it towards square leg for a single.
Shorter delivery on middle, Karunaratne defends it off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Thirimanne guides it to point for a single.
Looped up ball on middle, Karunaratne flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Flatter on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot towards point.
FOUR! First boundary of the innings and it has taken more than 21 overs to come. Shorter around off, Karunaratne cuts it through point for a boundary.
Flighted on off, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off which spun away from the batsman, Dimuth looks to defend but misses the ball.
Another flighted delivery on off spinning away, Dimuth looks to defend again but fails to put any bat on it.
LEG BYE! Full delivery on the pads, Dimuth looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads, the ball rolls towards fine leg for a single.

In the air but in no man's land. Tossed up on middle, Karunaratne goes for a big sweep but gets a top edge on it. The ball goes towards the fine leg region but there is no one there so it is safe. Two taken as the fielder from square leg cleans it up.
Loopy delivery on middle, Karunaratne comes down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flatter delivery on off, Dimuth plays it towards third man for a brace.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth comes down the track and flicks it but it falls just short of the short leg fielder.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth flicks it towards fine leg.
Shorter in length this time, Dimuth flicks it towards fine leg again. No run
Floated on off, Thirimanne blocks it out.
Peach of a ball! Somerville gives it air on off, Thirimanne lunges out and looks to defend but gets beaten. That was not far away from the outside edge.
Shorter on off, Thirimanne plays it towards point for one.
Flighted delivery on off stump, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Dimuth goes for the sweep but misses due to the spin on it.
Shorter in length outside off, Dimuth cuts it towards point. No run.
Flighted on middle and off, Thirimanne gets his front foot in the line of the ball and defends it to the on side, wide of short leg.
Thirimanne defends this flighted delivery towards square leg.
Shorter delivery on middle, Lahiru flicks it to square leg.
Flighted delivery on the off side, LT defends it to short leg.
Flighted delivery on middle, Lahiru tries to reverse sweep but the ball goes off his arm to the short fine leg fielder.
Looped up ball on middle, Thirimanne flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Flatter on off, Thirimanne defends it towards point.
Quicker and sharp turn on this one. It is on middle and leg, Thirimanne looks to defend but the ball spins in and hits him on the forearms.
Tossed up on off, Lahiru defends it off the front foot.

FOUR! First boundary of the innings for Thirimanne. It also brings up the fifty for Sri Lanka. Tossed up on off, Thirimanne gets down on one knee and sweeps it through the vacant square leg region for a boundary. Sri Lanka have had a solid start here as they find themselves 52/0. Need 216 more.
Floated on the stumps, Thirimanne follows the boundary with a calm defense.
Arm ball outside off, Thirimanne does not disturb it.

OHH! Flighted delivery on off which spun out off the rough and turned into the batsman, Dimuth looks to cut but gets an inside edge which just goes past the stumps towards fine leg. The batsmen take a brace
Tossed up on middle, Dimuth comes down the track and glances it wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Floated on off, Thirimanne keeps it out.
Loopy delivery on off, Dimuth defends it back to the bowler

APPEAL FOR LBW! Flighted delivery on off stump which spun away from the batsman. Thirimanne goes for the reverse sweep but misses it. The Kiwis appeal but nothing from the umpire. The Kiwis think of a review but opt against it. Unfortunately the replays show that the ball hit the gloves of the batsman on its way to the keeper.
Short delivery on the middle stump line, Thirimanne flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Flatter and spinning away, Karunaratne defends it with the spin towards the man at second slip.

Loosener but missed out. Short and spinning away around off, Dimuth gets on his back foot and looks to punch it wide of short cover. Williamson swiftly moves to his right and saves a certain boundary.
Flighted outside off, Dimuth looks to defend but misses.
On the stumps, Dimuth blocks it off the front foot.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Tosses it up on off, Karunaratne keeps it out to get through another over unscathed.
Looped up ball on off, Thirimanne plays it towards mid-wicket.
Comes down to this full delivery does Thirimanne and plays it towards mid on for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dimuth flicks it to the leg side.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth plays it to square leg and takes a single.
Loopy delivery on off which spun into the batsman, Lahiru tries to defend but misses and hits him on the pads which lobs off to short fine leg. The Kiwi players appeal but nothing from the umpire.
FOUR! Finally Thirimanne gets his reverse sweep right. It is a flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne plays the reverse and times it beautifully towards the cover-point region for a boundary.
Short around off, Dimuth runs it down to short third man.
Flighted around off, Karunaratne gets on his front foot and strokes it to cover.
Arm ball on off, Dimuth blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Dimuth calmly blocks it.
Gives this one air on middle and leg, DK pushes it to cover.
Tossed up around off, Karunaratne gets down on one knee and paddles it towards fine leg for a couple.
Comes around the wicket does Santner. It was a loopy ball on off, Thirimanne pushes it to cover and takes a single.
Full delivery which is converted to a full toss by Dimuth and it is played towards square leg for a brace. This is now the highest partnership in this Test match.
Shorter delivery on middle, Dimuth flicks it towards fine leg. No run.
Looped up ball on off, Dimuth dances down the track and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket for another brace. 200 runs required now.
Flighted delivery on middle, Karunaratne pushes it towards the long on fielder for a single.
Thirimanne defends this loopy ball back towards the bowler.
Floated on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.

FOUR! Hammered from Karunaratne. It is a flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth plays a lofted shot over the bowler's head and into the long off fence. Somerville jumps up to catch it but does not get a hand on it.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth defends it back to the bowler.

FIFTY FOR KARUNARATNE! What a knock this has been from the skipper! They are chasing a big total and they needed a bright start. Dimuth has given them just that. His 23rd in Test match cricket. He gets there with some luck. Flatter and shorter outside off, Karunaratne looks to cut but gets a thick bottom edge through BJ Watling's legs. The ball runs behind and the batsmen complete two runs. Just a mild celebration from the Lankan skipper, he knows that there is a long way to go in this Test match. Keeping his focus intact.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth blocks it out.
Looped up ball on off, Dimuth pushes it towards the point fielder and sets off for a quick single. With that, it is Tea on Day 4.
Shorter delivery on off stump spinning into the batsman, Dimuth slaps it towards the point region for a single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Lahiru plays it to point for a single.
Full delivery on middle, Dimuth comes down the track and plays it towards mid on and takes a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Thirimanne defends it off the front foot.
Shorter delivery on off, Thirimanne slaps it towards the cover-point region for a brace.
Flatter delivery on middle, LT defends it back to the bowler off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Full on off, Dimuth pushes it to mid off.
Full delivery on off, Karunaratne pushes it to mid off.
Full delivery on the middle stump line, Karunaratne pushes it back to the bowler.
Full length delivery on middle, DK defends it off the front foot.
On a good length on middle, Dimuth defends it towards mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on off, Lahiru looks to reverse sweep at first but changes his mind at the last moment and plays a drive towards cover for a brace.
Flighted delivery on off, Thirimanne guides it to third man and takes a single.
Full delivery on middle, Dimuth comes down the track and flicks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Looped up ball on off, Thirimanne defends it off the front foot towards the off side.
Flatter delivery on middle, Thirimanne defends it off the back foot.
OHH! Flighted delivery on middle, Lahiru tries to defend but gets an inside edge towards short leg. Latham dives forward, attempting to take the catch but it falls just short.
Back of a length ball around off, Dimuth pulls it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Full and a hint of away movement. Lahiru looks to defend and it goes off the outer half of his bat to the right of short third man.
FOUR! Class written all over it. Full outside off, Thirimanne gets on the front foot and drives it through point for a glorious boundary. The score now is into the 90s.
Follows it up with a solid front foot defense.
Full on off, Thirimanne just guides it to mid off.
Another good looking drive but this is straight to the man at cover.
Full toss on off, Thirimanne will feel that he missed on that as he could play it only as far as mid off for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne defends it off the front foot.
Looped up ball on off, Thirimanne drives it beautifully towards the cover region and before the fielders can clean it up, the batsman takes three.
Flighted delivery on off, Karunaratne comes down the track and pushes it to mid on and takes a single.
Looped up ball on off, Lahiru goes for the sweep towards square leg and takes a single.

Ajaz bowls it with a flight on middle, Dimuth goes for the defense but gets an inside edge towards short leg. Tom Latham is standing a little deep than the usual position and it falls way short of him.
Floated on the stumps, Thirimanne blocks it off the front foot.
Tossed up around off, Lahiru defends it off the front foot.
On the stumps, Thirimanne keeps it out.
Short and turning in, Lahiru looks to defend but misses and the ball strikes him on his gut.
Beauty! Floated outside off, Lahiru looks to defend but gets beaten all ends up.
Floated on middle, Thirimanne strokes it to long on for one.
Floats one outside off, Thirimanne gets his front foot across the off pole and pads it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Excellent fielding from Boult! Saves a run for his side. Flighted outside off, Thirimanne sweeps it through square leg. It looks like the ball will go to the fence but Boult runs in from mid-wicket and shows his athleticism. He covers the ground and pulls it back just before the ropes. 100 comes up for Sri Lanka.
Loopy delivery on middle, Karunaratne plays it back to the bowler.
Shorter delivery on the off stump line, Dimuth flicks it to short leg.

DROPPED BY LATHAM! Latham is the culprit here. It is a flighted delivery on off, Dimuth comes down the track and tries to flick but the ball goes off the inside edge towards short leg who makes a mess of it. Big break for the Sri Lankan skipper and he has to make use of the opportunity. Karunaratne dropped on 58.
Floated on off, Thirimanne gets behind the ball and blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Lahiru keeps it out.
Darts one on off, Thirimanne looks to defend but the ball goes off the inner half of his bat towards backward square leg for a single.
Shorter delivery on off stump, Dimuth cuts but straight to point. No run.

MISSED STUMPING! Flighted delivery on off, Dimuth comes down the track to flick it but fails to get any bat on it. Watling makes a hash of it as he fails to collect the ball cleanly. New Zealand will rue these missed chances.
Looped up ball on middle, Dimuth flicks it to fine leg and takes a single.
Flighted on off, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, Dimuth turns it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Short and spinning in. This has turned a lot actually. It starts from outside off and spins in. Thirimanne looks to defend but misses and the ball hits him around the box.
Floated on middle and off, Thirimanne sweeps it to square leg.
On the stumps, kept out by Thirimanne.

FOUR BYES! That has beaten everybody. Tossed up on middle and off, it grips off the surface. Thirimanne looks to play the reverse sweep but misses. The ball misses the stumps and beats Watling and goes to the fine leg fence.
Flatter delivery on off, Dimuth rocks back and cuts it towards point and takes a single.

IN THE AIR... SAFE! Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne top edges his attempted slog sweep and luckily for him it falls in no man's land at deep square leg. The ball drops and doesn't move much as the outfield is a bit heavy due to all the rain. By the time the fielder mops it up, the batters take two.
Looped up ball on off, Thirimanne attempts to defend but is hit on the pads.
Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne defends it off the front foot.
Loopy delivery on off, LT defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter delivery on middle, Thirimanne flicks it to fine leg and takes a single.
Darted around the pads, Thirimanne sweeps it straight to leg slip.
Flatter around off, Thirimanne looks to defend but gets hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal but the impact was outside off.
This time sweeps it to square leg for one.
Full delivery on middle, Dimuth pushes this towards mid on and takes off for a quick single.
Loopy delivery on off, Thirimanne defends it towards the cover fielder and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Karunaratne pushes it towards cover and takes a single.

Uppish but safe! Short and outside off, spinning away with extra bounce, Karunaratne cuts it in the air and it falls safely between the two fielders at the point region. It sneaks through for a couple of runs.
Fullish and on off, driven down the ground but straight to mid off.
Flighted delivery, full and around off, Dimuth leans and defends it with an angled bat to point.
Extra flight this time, the length is full and around off, Dimuth drives but finds the cover fielder.
A shade short in length on off, Karunaratne gets back to cut but finds the point fielder again.
Flatter and quicker on off, it's blocked off the back foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Thirimanne tries to defend but gets hit on the pads. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but not given.
Looped up delivery on middle, Thirimanne looks to sweep but gets hit on the arm and the ball rolls to short fine leg.
Looped up delivery on off, Thirimanne blocks it out.
Fuller delivery on off, Thirimanne goes for the sweep again and times it well but it hits Latham on the way. The batsman checks on the fielder if he is fine. Tom is doing good.

FOUR! 6th half century for Thirimanne in Tests. It's a shorter delivery on the middle stump line, Thirimanne flicks it past the fine leg fielder for a boundary. It has been a fidgety innings from Thirimanne but an important one in the context of the game. This is his first fifty since 2017. Welcome fifty!
Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne plays it towards point.
Flighted outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Shorter on off, Dimuth strokes it with the spin towards cover. He looks for a single but Lahiru says no.
Flighted delivery on off, Karunaratne keeps it out.
Darts one on the pads, Karunaratne flicks it to the on side for a single.
Floats it on the stumps, Thirimanne defends it off the front foot.
On the stumps, Thirimanne keeps it out to get through the over.
Full delivery on the off stump line, Dimuth pushes it uppishly but the ball falls short of the mid on fielder.
Full delivery on middle, DK flicks it uppishly to square leg for a single.
Short ball on the body, Thirimanne rocks back and defends it towards point.
Short ball on the leg stump, Thirimanne flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple.
Back of a length ball on off, Thirimanne defends it with soft hands off the back foot. The ball goes to the off side and they get a single.
Short ball on off, DK pulls it to square leg and keeps the strike.
Short delivery outside the off stump, Dimuth cuts it straight to point.
Quicker delivery from Somerville, it is bowled on the middle stump and Dimuth just gets his bat down in time to block it out.
Loopy ball outside off, DK leaves it alone.
Looped up ball on off, Dimuth defends it back to the bowler.
Short delivery outside off stump, Dimuth looks to cut but fails to put bat on it.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
Short ball on off, Thirimanne pulls it wide of deep mid-wicket for a couple.
On the pads, Lahiru flicks it fine down the leg side for a single.
On the body, Dimuth glances it down to fine leg and gets another brace.
Short ball on the body, Dimuth pulls hard but straight to the square leg fielder.
Boult loses his line here, it is a full delivery which is bowled outside the leg stump, Dimuth looks to flick but misses.
Good length delivery on the pads, Dimuth flicks it to fine leg and takes a single.
Floated on off, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up outside off, Karunaratne defends it with soft hands. The ball hits the outside edge of the bat but falls short of second slip.
Loopy delivery on off, Dimuth defends it to the off side.
Flighted delivery outside off, Karunaratne leaves it alone.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dimuth defends it back to the bowler.
Bowls a flighted delivery outside off, Dimuth lets it go back to the keeper.
Starts with a loopy delivery on middle, spinning down, Lahiru looks to flick but misses.
Full delivery on middle, Thirimanne flicks it to mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on off, Thirimanne defends it towards cover.
Looped up ball on middle, Lahiru defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, LT blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Thirimanne defends it back to the bowler. Santner starts with a maiden.
Starts with a flighted delivery wide outside off. It turns back in from there as Karunaratne pads it away. A stifled appeal but it dies down quickly.
Fuller and on off, Dimuth drives it straight back to the bowler.
Uses his feet to reach the pitch of the delivery and then clips it with the turn. Finds mid on.
Flighted delivery on off, Dimuth looks to flick but gets hit on the front pad.
Loopy delivery on off, Karunaratne comes down the track and plays it towards the mid on region and takes the single. First runs of the day for the hosts.
Flighted delivery on off, Thirimanne sweeps it towards the mid-wicket region and gets his first run of the day.
Nicely flighted delivery, pitching full around off, Lahiru lunges and blocks it safely.
Good shot! Tossed up ball landing in the rough outside off, Thirimanne brings out the reverse sweep and places it behind backward point for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth flicks it to mid-wicket and crosses over for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle spinning into the batsman, Thirimanne pushes it to short leg.
Looped up ball on middle, Thirimanne blocks it out.
Quicker delivery on off, Thirimanne defends it off the back foot towards the off side.
Walks down the track to a full ball and drives it back. The bowler moves across to his left to stop the ball.
Uses the spin this time and gently flicks it in the direction of the mid on fielder.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dimuth flicks it towards the mid-wicket region and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne blocks it out.
Ajaz bowls a loopy delivery on middle, LT plays a reverse sweep towards the cover region and crosses over for a single.

FOUR! First boundary of the day for the hosts. It is a flighted delivery on the off pole, Dimuth flicks it with the spin towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. Excellent shot this. 125 more needed for the hosts.
Nicely flighted and full outside off, drawing the batsman forward, Thirimanne pushes it to point.
Flighted delivery on off, Thirimanne leaves it alone.
Floated delivery outside the off stump line, Thirimanne at first looks to cut but pulls out at the last moment.
Looped up ball on middle, LT defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne blocks it out.
Shorter delivery on middle, Thirimanne plays it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth comes down the track and plays it to short mid-wicket.
Flighted delivery on middle, Karunaratne looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads.

DROPPED! Another catch dropped by Latham. It is a loopy delivery on middle, Dimuth looks to flick which went towards the short leg fielder who does not hold onto it. Not the first time Tom has dropped a catch in this innings.
Flatter delivery on middle, Dimuth blocks it out.
Short delivery on middle, Dimuth reverse sweeps it towards the point region and takes a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Lahiru flicks it towards square leg and takes another single.

Pushes this one quicker through the air. Lands it full and around off, gets it to spin away as well. Karunaratne is on the front foot as he pushes at it with an angled bat. Does well to do so with soft hands and edges it wide of second slip.
Defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flatter one, a touch short and on off, Dimuth blocks it off his back foot to the off side.
Another delivery fired in. It's short and close to off stump. Karunaratne stays back to cut but misses. Too close to the body, that.
Leans forward to a full ball and defends it on the leg side.

FOUR! Slapped away! Somerville continues to bowl flatter but this one is shorter too. Plenty of width on offer and the Lankan skipper has whacked it towards backward point. The fielder there is not proactive enough to cut it off. A boundary results.
Shorter delivery on the off stump line, Thirimanne guides it to third man for a single.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dimuth comes down the track and looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.
Loopy delivery on middle, Karunaratne looks to sweep but misses the ball to get hit on the pads.
Works it with the spin on the leg side, finds mid-wicket.

SIX! DK has nailed it! He shimmies down the track and goes with the spin. Lovely flourish of his bat across the line and he sends it flying all the way over mid-wicket. 150 comes up for Sri Lanka, another 113 needed!
Once again the Lankan skipper jumps down the track and this time he keeps his shot all along the ground. Eases it to long on for one.
Flighted delivery on off, Dimuth drives it towards the cover fielder and takes off for a single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Thirimanne defends it back to the bowler.
Floated delivery outside the off stump line, Thirimanne leaves it alone.
Shorter delivery on off, Lahiru defends it towards the off side.
Another flighted delivery outside the off stump line, LT lets it go to the keeper.
Looped up ball on middle, Thirimanne blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on off, Dimuth defends it to the off side.

Big shout for LBW! Flighted delivery on middle spinning into the batsman, Dimuth looks to flick but gets hit on the front pad. The Kiwi players put in a huge appeal but it is turned down. They think of a review but opt against it and rightly so as the ball was drifting down the leg stump.
Shorter delivery on middle, Dimuth flicks it to short leg.
Flighted delivery on middle, Dimuth comes down the track and plays it towards mid on for a single.
Looped up ball on middle, Thirimanne flicks it off his pads towards short leg.
Shorter delivery outside the off stump, Thirimanne rocks back and slaps it through the cover region and run through for three. Thirimanne will keep the strike for the next over.
Darts it in, very full and around off, Thirimanne gets right behind the line and blocks it on the off side.

OUT! Good review by New Zealand and they have managed to break this massive opening stand. It's a nicely tossed up delivery, landing full around middle and leg. Thirimanne sees the line and length closely and finds it good enough to opt for the sweep shot. He goes down on one knee to execute it but the ball straightens after landing, beats his bat and pings him on the pads. The appeal for an lbw follows but the umpire remains unmoved. Kane Williamson goes for the DRS and to his delight everything is fine in the replays. No bat involved, pitching in line, impact in line and it's hitting the leg pole. End of a fine knock by Lahiru, a career saving one? That only time will tell.

Nervy beginning for Kusal! Somerville straightaway gets it to spin and bounce into the batsman from around middle. Mendis tries to flick but it takes the inside half of his blade and flies just past short leg.
FOUR! That's the way to deal with extra spin or bounce. Just don't allow it to do its bit. Mendis is down the track in a flash and heaves it over wide mid on for a boundary.
Fuller and on middle, gently pushed across the line on the leg side.

SIX! This one has travelled all the way! Kusal Mendis has come out with some positive intent. Shows fancy footwork once again. A flighted full ball around off, Mendis dances down the track, goes with the spin and powers it over long on. 10 runs and a wicket from the over, an eventful one! Under 100 needed now.
Walks down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Quicker one outside off, skidding off the surface, Karunaratne plays it late and guides it fine past first slip for a couple of runs.
Helps it off his pads to square leg for one.
Flatter and shorter on off, Mendis tries to cut but mistimes it on the off side.

OUT! Mendis batted like a train on fire but the Kiwis have extinguished that fire pretty quickly. Ajaz serves a tossed up ball outside off, the length is very full around off, not quite there to slog but Mendis still attempts it by going down on one knee. Fails to get it from the middle of the bat and it flies straight into the hands of Jeet Raval at mid-wicket. Good sharp reaction catch by the Kiwi opener. Sri Lanka have lost a couple of quick wickets here and need to watch out for a collapse.
Mathews has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted delivery on off, Dimuth drives it to cover.
Off spinner on the off stump line, Dimuth plays it towards point.
Short delivery on the middle stump line, Dimuth flicks it to fine leg and takes a single. Moves to 96 with that single.

OHH! Mathews gets off the mark with a streaky single. It is a flighted delivery on middle, Angelo looks to flick but due to the spin on it, he flicks it uppishly towards short leg. Latham is unable to react quickly and the ball goes through his hands towards square leg.
Looped up ball on off, Dimuth defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Karunaratne defends it off the front foot.
Fires in a flatter and very full ball on off, Angelo pushes it through mid off for a single.
Defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Extra turn and bounce from outside off, Dimuth fails to work it away and is hit high on the front leg.
Skips down the track to a full ball and drives it to long on for a single.
Floated and full on off, Mathews is forward in defense.
Nicely flighted delivery, full and on off, Mathews draws forward in defense.
Flighted delivery outside the off stump line, Dimuth leaves it alone.
Loopy delivery on off, Dimuth defends it to cover.
Short delivery on the off stump line, Dimuth rocks back and cuts it straight to point.
Flatter delivery on middle, DK flicks it to fine leg and takes a single. He moves closer to his century with that.
Shorter delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it to square leg. No run.
Loopy delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it to mid-wicket.
Very full in length around off, Karunaratne knocks it down to long on for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Mathews defends it towards the point region and takes a single.

FOUR! 9th Test hundred for Dimuth Karunaratne, fifth while batting in the third or fourth innings of a Test match. That tells volumes about his calibre. The pitch is not an easy one to bat on but the Lankan skipper has applied himself and put his side in the driver's seat in this tricky run chase. He reaches there by dancing down the track and heaving a full ball with the spin. Lovely connection and it's a boundary at mid-wicket. Dimuth raises his bat in celebration. Wonderful knock so far and he would love to be there till the end.
Looped up ball on off, DK follows the boundary with a single by forcing it down to long on.
Flighted delivery on off, Mathews blocks it out.

FOUR! Poor bowling from Ajaz. It is a short delivery outside the off stump line, Mathews rocks back and slaps it through the point region for his first boundary of the innings. Ajaz has been really expensive today.
Advances down the track to a full ball and defends it back to the bowler.

EDGED! Safe. Sharp turn from the rough outside off, there is extra bounce as well. Karunaratne moves back to play at it but it takes the outside half of his bat and flies behind. Taylor stretches low to his left at first slip but the ball falls just wide of his big palms. It sneaks past him then and the batsmen take a couple of runs.
Flighted delivery on the off pole line, Dimuth flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Looped up ball on middle, Mathews defends it towards the off side.
Shorter delivery on middle, Mathews blocks it out off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on middle, Angelo blocks it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery on off, Dimuth drives it towards mid off and takes a quick single.
Flatter delivery on the off stump line, Mathews defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Mathews pushes this one down to mid off for a single.
Loopy delivery on the off stump, Dimuth defends it towards the point region.
Looped up ball on off, Dimuth prods forward and drives it towards the mid off region and crosses over.
Flighted delivery on middle, Mathews attempts to defend but fails to put any bat on it. Angelo gets hit on the pads.
Flighted and full on off, Karunaratne walks forward and drives it through mid on for a run.
Defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Short and outside off, Mathews cuts it towards cover-point for one.
FOUR! Poor bowling! A rank long hop outside off, plenty of width there, Karunaratne camps back and slaps it through cover-point for a boundary. 200 comes up for Sri Lanka!
Quicker one and this time it's on the pads of the batsman, Dimuth helps it to mid-wicket and rotates the strike.
Fullish and on off, defended watchfully to end the over. Going on smoothly, Sri Lanka.
Flighted delivery on the off stump line, Dimuth defends it towards the point fielder.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dimuth plays a crafty sweep shot towards the fine leg fielder and takes a brace.
Looped up ball on off, Dimuth defends it off the front foot to the off side.
Shorter in length this time on off, Dimuth defends it off the back foot.
Floated delivery on the off stump line, Karunaratne guides it to third man. No run.
Loopy delivery on off, Dimuth blocks it towards the point region.
On a good length on middle, Mathews defends it back to the bowler.
Good length delivery outside the off stump line, Mathews pushes this one down to mid off.
Full delivery on the off stump line, Mathews defends this to cover.
On a length on middle, Mathews blocks it out off the back foot.
Bowls a good length delivery on the pads, Mathews flicks it towards square leg and moves to the other end.
Good length delivery outside the off stump, Dimuth does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
Big turn! This is why he should have bowled earlier. Flighted delivery which spins a mile, Mathews goes for the flick but misses and it goes past the keeper for a couple of byes.
Loopy delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it towards the leg side for a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Dimuth defends it off the front foot.
Looped up ball on off, Dimuth plays a sweep towards square leg and takes another single.
Flighted delivery on middle, Mathews blocks it out.
Shorter delivery on middle, Mathews flicks it towards square leg for a single.
On a good length on off, Mathews defends off the front foot towards mid off.
Good length delivery on middle, Angelo pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length on the middle stump line, Mathews blocks it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Mathews defends it towards the leg side.
On a length around off, AM drives it to mid off and takes a quick single.
On a good length outside the off stump, Dimuth leaves it alone.
Flighted delivery on off, Mathews blocks it off the back foot.
Loopy delivery on the off stump line, Mathews flicks it towards fine leg. No run.
Full delivery on middle, Mathews comes down the track and pushes it towards long on and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Dimuth goes for sweep but plays it uppishly towards the square leg region. A couple taken. They need 53 more runs now.

Short of a length delivery outside the off stump, Dimuth first thinks of going for a traditional sweep but changes his mind after seeing the length. He tries to pull then but gets beaten by the away spin.
Loopy delivery on middle, Dimuth defends it towards the cover region.
Lands it on a length outside off, Mathews pushes it with gentle hands to short cover.
On a length and close to the off pole, Angelo punches it from the crease and it bounces over the short cover fielder. There is one more fielder behind who makes the stop.
Hurls across a length delivery in the channel outside off, going straight on, Mathews guards his stumps with a front foot stride and then makes a leave.
Pushed to the cover region by the batsman. A very watchful approach by the former Lankan skipper.
Southee pitches it up and outside off, inviting the drive, Mathews goes for it but finds the cover fielder.
Fullish and outside off, it's stroked off the front foot to short cover.
Flighted delivery on the off stump line, Dimuth drives it to point.
Flighted delivery on the off stump, Dimuth sweeps it to square leg and takes a single. Dimuth has not allowed the spinners to settle here.
Shorter length on middle, Mathews flicks it to fine leg.
Another short delivery on off, Mathews rocks back and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery on middle, Angelo pushes this one down to long on for a single.
Flighted delivery outside the off stump line, Dimuth sweeps again towards square leg for a single. 50 more runs are required for the hosts.

OUT! A wicket against the run of play! Just a little lapse in concentration for the Sri Lankan skipper and he is caught behind. Southee bowls this one from wide of the crease and hurls it in the channel outside off. Karunaratne reaches out for it, a loose waft that, as he attempts to push inside the line. Gets a thin outside edge behind and Watling takes a regulation catch. Dimuth is congratulated by the Kiwi players on his way back to the pavilion. Captain's knock, truly. 50 more needed for a win.
Width offered outside off, Perera goes hard at it but hits it straight to the cover fielder.
Swing and a miss! Perera will go after anything outside off. Southee tempts him with a delivery in the channel outside off, Kusal winds up for a big shot but fails to connect.
Patience shown this time. Fullish and outside off, Perera has decided to leave it untouched.
That's more like it, quips Russel Arnold on air. A delivery in the zone outside off, Kusal takes his front leg forward before making another leave. No need to do anything silly.

FOUR! Kusal Perera was itching to go after anything wide outside off. Gets another one where he likes and throws his bat at it. His willow turns at the point of impact and that assisted the placement there. It hurries through point and beats the diving attempt by a fielder near the fence.
Flighted delivery on middle, Mathews dances down the track and flicks it mid-wicket.
Short delivery on middle, Angelo pushes this one down towards the deep mid-wicket region for a single.
OHH! Lucky! It is a flighted delivery around off, Perera goes for the cut but inside edges it almost onto the off stump. It goes in between the keeper's legs towards the third man region for a brace.

FOUR! Excellent shot from Perera. It is a loopy delivery on off, Perera comes down the track and hits it past the diving mid on fielder for a boundary. Perera is looking dangerous here. 20 more minutes of him and the game will be over for the visitors.

SAFE! Kusal Perera tries to be fancy with his reverse-batted shot but fails to make proper connection. The ball has flown from something and the second slip fielder has caught it. The umpire has given it out as well. Perera waits before taking the referral. He consults Angelo and then takes the DRS. A bit odd. He must be knowing if that hit his gloves or bat. Anyway. Is there bat? Is there glove? Nothing on the Ultra Edge and it has struck him on the forearm, just above the wrist band. As per the norm, they check for the lbw as well but the impact is with the umpire's call.
Uppish but safe! Spinning away from the batsman, Kusal tries to drill his drive through covers but it takes the outside half of his bat and rolls to the right of the point fielder.
On a good length outside off, Mathews lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on the off stump line, Mathews punches this one down to mid off and takes a single.
FOUR! Kusal wants to finish this quickly. On a good length this one from Southee. Kusal hoicks this over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary. KP is in the mood today.
On a good length ball outside off, Perera leaves it alone.
BEAUTIFUL! Another good length delivery from Southee, Perera looks to poke at it but changes his mind at the last moment. He gets his bat out and lets it go to the keeper.

FOUR! Beautiful shot from Perera. Southee bowls this fuller on middle, Kusal comes one step down and plays an excellent drive straight down the ground for a boundary. Perera has moved to 18 off just 13 balls. 30 more runs required for the hosts. With Perera in, it looks likely that the match will finish before Lunch.
Jumps out of the crease to a full ball around off and then defends it back to the bowler.
Shortish and on middle, skidding down, Angelo tries to work it around but fails to connect.
Uses his feet once more and this time he has eased it down through mid on for a run. 7 minutes to go for Lunch, 29 needed more. They have the option of extending the first session.

PERERA IS SAFE AGAIN! Tossed up ball landing full around off, Perera tries to play the reverse sweep but fails to make any connection. He is pinched on the back leg, they appeal but the umpire remains unmoved. New Zealand review the decision but the Hawk Eye shows that the impact was outside the line of off stump.
Flatter and shorter on middle, punched through covers for a run.
Shortish and around off, Mathews turns it through square leg for one.

Good start from Boult. It is an inswinging delivery on the off stump line, Mathews looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The Kiwis appeal but the umpire is unmoved. The replays show that it came off the inside edge.
Full delivery on the middle stump line, Mathews blocks it to square leg.
On a good length ball on off, Mathews drives this towards mid off. No run.
Good length delivery on middle, Mathews plays it to the cover region and takes a single.
OHH! A terrific yorker with a hint of away shape, Perera is late to get his bat down and the ball goes through. It just misses the off stump by a whisker.

FOUR! Hammered! It is a good length ball outside off, Perera charges down the track and hammers it over the cover fielder for a boundary. Perera moves to 23 with that boundary. The hosts need 22 more runs.
Spinning down the leg side, Mathews tries to flick but misses. The keeper collects the ball but Angelo does well to plant his back leg inside the crease just in time.
FOUR! Poor delivery and the watchful Mathews has decided to punish it. Short and on middle, Angelo rocks back and pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Sliding down the leg side, Mathews fails to work it away.
Quicker and on the pads, helped out on the leg side.
Gets forward and defends it towards short leg.
Comes from 'round the wicket and delivers it around off, Mathews walks down the track and then pads it away.
BEAUTIFUL! Another outswinger from Boult. It is a good length delivery outside the off stump, Perera pokes at it and luckily does not get an edge on it.

OUT! CAUGHT! An entertaining cameo comes to an end from Kusal Perera. It is a good length delivery on middle and leg, Perera dances down the track with the intention of going big over the leg side. But it doesn't come properly off his bat and he ends up handing a simple catch to Santner at mid on. Kusal was trying to finish things quickly and perished in that effort. 18 more required.
On a good length on middle, de Silva flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on middle, Dhananjaya defends it to square leg.
FOUR! Crashed! It is a length ball way outside off, de Silva goes for it and hammers it between the point and cover fielders for a boundary. Dhananjaya gets off the mark with that shot.
On a good length on middle, Dhananjaya defends it towards the leg side.
Good length delivery by Southee first up, Mathews flicks it to square leg.
Short ball outside the off stump, Mathews rocks back and cuts it towards point for a single.
Full delivery on the off stump line, Dhananjaya pushes it to cover. No run.

FOUR! Lovely shot! Southee bowls this one on the pads, Dhananjaya flicks this towards the square leg fence. The fielder from fine leg comes running and tries to make a diving stop but his leg gets stuck on the ground. The ball goes through and into the fence. 9 more runs needed.
Back of a length delivery around off, de Silva punches this one off the back foot.
On a good length ball outside the off stump, Dhananjaya leaves it alone.
Bouncer! Mathews sees it and ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on off, Mathews is in no hurry and calmly defends it off his back foot.
Fuller on off, Angelo pushes it to mid off.
Short from Southee, Mathews eases his pull towards fine leg for one.
On top of middle, Dhananjaya defends it with a straight bat.

Full on off, Dhananjaya drives it straight but the bat turns in his hands and he ends up mistiming it past the stumps at the non-striker's end. The batsmen come back for the second as the fielder from mid off cleans it up. Just 6 needed now.
Good length ball around off, Mathews stands tall and punches it to cover.
On off, Mathews defends it off the front foot.
Straight as an arrow. Full ball on middle, Mathews plays a good looking straight drive but it is too straight as the ball ricochets off the stumps and goes wide of mid on. Single taken.
FOUR! Just a run away from a historic chase here in Galle. Short ball on off, de Silva gets on his back foot and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
No hurry as de Silva is not interested in playing this length ball outside off.
Good length ball outside off, Dhananjaya calmly leaves it alone.
That is it! Mathews takes Sri Lanka home. Good length ball on middle and off, Angelo shuffles and turns it behind square on the leg side to seal the game. SRI LANKA WIN BY 6 WICKETS!
